{"type":"message","id":"e8194a2b","parentId":"44dcfaeb","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:11:25.350Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Clarifying skill search options**\n\nI need to respond to the user who asked for help finding a skill. I believe there's a skill-finding tool available, but it seems like there might be some confusion about its name. It appears the tool \"functions.find_skills\" isn't correctly set up or named. I could guide the user by saying I can search for existing skills or suggest creating a custom skill instead. Plus, I can use the web search to look up skills related to the specific query!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_nOsgco0oYqxDomMtHC9nBbi6","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"OpenClaw skill outfit recommendation from image","count":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":1414,"output":340,"cacheRead":10752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12506,"cost":{"input":-1414,"output":-340,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1754}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772323879829}}
{"type":"message","id":"cbf3d553","parentId":"e8194a2b","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:11:25.357Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_nOsgco0oYqxDomMtHC9nBbi6","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"error\": \"missing_brave_api_key\",\n  \"message\": \"web_search needs a Brave Search API key. Run `openclaw configure --section web` to store it, or set BRAVE_API_KEY in the Gateway environment.\",\n  \"docs\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/web\"\n}"}],"details":{"error":"missing_brave_api_key","message":"web_search needs a Brave Search API key. Run `openclaw configure --section web` to store it, or set BRAVE_API_KEY in the Gateway environment.","docs":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/web"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772323885354}}
{"type":"message","id":"175f2f59","parentId":"cbf3d553","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:11:31.625Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Determining outfit types**\n\nI'm thinking about what types of outfits the user might need. The budget is important too, as well as the occasion and the overall tone they want to convey. I wonder if they’re looking for something casual, formal, or maybe a mix. Let's proceed with gathering more details so I can provide tailored suggestions that fit their needs perfectly!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I can help, but I can’t search for existing skills right now because Brave Search API key isn’t configured in your environment. If you want, I can draft and build a custom skill outline to do exactly what you described (image-to-outfit recommendations) and we can implement it locally.\n\nProposed approach for a \"Macy: outfit-from-photo\" skill\n- Input: Macy uploads a photo (front/profile view works best).\n- Vision steps:\n  - Detect clothing items, colors, and approximate style (casual, formal, boho, etc.).\n  - Optional: detect context (season, occasion) if provided.\n- Recommendation engine:\n  - Map detected styles/colors to a curated outfit catalog (tops, bottoms, shoes, accessories).\n  - Suggest 3 complete outfits with rationale (e.g., color harmony, occasion fit, layering options).\n- Privacy safeguards:\n  - Process locally or anonymize images before any external lookup.\n- Outputs:\n  - Image-based summary + 3 outfit sets with links to similar items (if you want shopping integration).\n  - Quick tips (color pairing, fit notes).\n\nQuestions to tailor it\n1) Where will Macy upload the image (e.g., a private vault, a simple file drop in the app, or via a chat message)?\n2) What kind of outfits should be prioritized (casual, work, formal, date night, wedding guest, etc.)?\n3) Any constraints (budget range, preferred brands, size info, color preferences, or body positivity considerations)?\n4) Do you want external shopping links included, or should the output be purely styling suggestions without purchase references?\n\nIf you’d like, I can proceed with a concrete file structure and sample code or a detailed spec you can hand off to a developer. What would you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":238,"output":772,"cacheRead":12032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13042,"cost":{"input":-238,"output":-772,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1010}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772323885357}}
