{"type":"message","id":"354e7ab0","parentId":"6ba1d35f","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:24:35.051Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning optimization strategy**\n\nI should discuss creating a local optimization resembling \"Copilot Pro / Claude Pro\" to minimize token usage. My plan includes developing a lightweight local agent featuring caching, model routing, context window management, using cheaper models, and managing a token budget. I want to ask clarifying questions about the preferred model alias, whether to utilize openrouter-auto, deployment options (local vs cloud), and privacy considerations. Finally, I can offer to draft the SKILL.md as the next step.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Nice pick. Building a local “Copilot Pro” vibe to cut token burn is very doable. Here’s a concrete plan and what I’d need to tailor it for you.\n\nWhat I’ll aim to build\n- Token-saver routing: smartly route queries to cheaper models when full power isn’t needed, with fallbacks to higher models for tough tasks.\n- Context management: persistent, compact context so you don’t repeat boilerplate prompts or long histories each time.\n- Lazy/partial tools: only fetch what’s necessary (e.g., cache recent results, reuse prior summaries).\n- Local orchestration: a small coordinator that you can run on your machine (or a minimal cloud) to minimize external calls and keep costs predictable.\n- Simple budget dashboard: track monthly token usage and costs, with alerts if you’re nearing a cap.\n- Optional: a “pause-for-review” toggle so you can inspect before expensive calls.\n\nProposed MVP scope\n- Input handling: you give a prompt; we decide which model to call.\n- Model routing: use a cheap model for drafting, then optionally refine with a higher-power model.\n- Context cache: store recent threads, key decisions, and commonly reused snippets locally.\n- Skippable tools: if a task doesn’t need live web access, skip web searches to save tokens.\n- Output: concise, actionable results with a quick summary of reasoning style used.\n\nQuestions to tailor it\n1) Which models do you want to route through? (e.g., cheap local/remote model for drafts + Claude-like higher-power for reviews)\n2) Do you prefer self-contained local processing or a lightweight cloud agent (to keep costs predictable but still fast)?\n3) How aggressive should the token budget be? (e.g., target < 5K tokens per session, or monthly cap)\n4) Do you want built-in web capability as an opt-in feature (with a hard guardrail to prevent runaway costs)?\n5) Any must-have privacy constraints (data never leaves your environment, or anonymized usage)?\n\nWhat I can deliver next\n- Draft a SKILL.md for an “OpenCopilot Pro” skill you can install/run in OpenClaw, including:\n  - Input spec and defaults\n  - Model routing policy\n  - Context management approach\n  - Budget/cost reporting\n  - Privacy guardrails\n  - Sample dialogues and fallback behavior\n- Provide a minimal deployment plan (local app or container) and a lightweight tech stack (e.g., Node.js/Python microservice, local cache, simple UI).\n\nWould you like me to draft the SKILL.md and a brief MVP backlog now, or would you prefer I propose a concrete architecture first (models, caching strategy, and data flows)?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":16967,"output":729,"cacheRead":1536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19232,"cost":{"input":-16967,"output":-729,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-17696}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772324667722}}
