{"type":"message","id":"f09c5dcf","parentId":"bf5d797d","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:27:42.287Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning daily digest conversion**\n\nI'm considering how to convert the Copilot Pro concept into a daily email digest. It should be concise and include components like report content, data sources, delivery schedule, and privacy considerations. I need to ask clarifying questions about the user’s email address, preferred delivery time, content granularity, metrics, attachment format, and opt-in preferences. My MVP could generate the digest via a script using local context and token usage. I wonder if we should use Gmail, as the user has that pipeline set up. I'll also include an outline and MVP backlog in the proposal.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Nice. Delivering a daily, detailed email report is a clean MVP for the Copilot Pro idea. Here’s a concrete plan you can act on.\n\nWhat the daily email report would include\n- Summary of token usage and costs for the previous day\n- Highlights of major tasks or prompts you ran\n- Model routing insights (which prompts used cheap vs. expensive models)\n- Key decisions and outcomes from open tasks\n- Suggested next actions to save tokens (e.g., use draft mode, skip web searches)\n- Optional: a short privacy/usage note and any anomalies\n\nDelivery details\n- Delivery time: set a fixed daily time (e.g., 7:00 AM local) or a time you prefer\n- Destination: your email address (Gmail-based pipeline you already have)\n- Format: plain text digest, with a concise bullet layout; optionally a lightweight HTML version\n- Attachments: optional CSV/Markdown report of daily metrics\n\nData sources and workflow (MVP)\n- Source data:\n  - Your session logs (which prompts were run)\n  - Token counts per model used\n  - Any web fetch or tool usage (to attribute cost)\n- Processing:\n  - Run a daily batch that aggregates yesterday’s activity\n  - Produce a human-friendly digest and recommended cost-saving actions\n- Output:\n  - Email body (and optional subject line like “OpenCopilot Pro — Daily Digest: YYYY-MM-DD”)\n  - Optional internal report (CSV/Markdown) for archiving\n\nPrivacy and security\n- Keep sensitive prompt content minimal in the digest; show only summaries unless you opt-in to full logs\n- Store only essential history for the digest; auto-purge older than a configurable window\n- If you want, we can keep everything local and generate the email content from a summarized cache instead of raw prompts\n\n MVP backlog (high-level)\n- Day 1: Define exact digest fields, sample output, and delivery time. Wire a basic script to read yesterday’s activity and generate a text digest.\n- Day 2: Integrate with Gmail sending (re-use your existing Gmail pipeline or a simple SMTP flow). Schedule the daily job.\n- Day 3: Add model-routing summary and token-cost metrics in the digest. Include “cost-saving tips” section.\n- Day 4: Add privacy controls and an audience toggle (full prompts vs. just summaries).\n- Day 5+: Polish formatting, add an optional HTML version, and add user-configurable settings (time, content depth).\n\nQuestions to tailor specifics\n1) What’s the exact email address to send to, and what time would you like the daily digest?\n2) What depth do you want in the digest? (High-level summary + 3-5 bullet insights vs. detailed prompts and tokens)\n3) Should we include exact token counts and model names, or just a plain cost estimate and recommendations?\n4) Do you want an optional “detailed logs” toggle in the email (e.g., a link to a private vault or a separate attachment) or keep everything in the body?\n5) Any must-have sections (e.g., weather/briefing summaries, task status, upcoming deadlines) included in every day’s report?\n\nWhat I can deliver next\n- A complete SKILL.md outline for an “OpenCopilot DailyDigest” skill that:\n  - Accepts your delivery address and time\n  - Reads yesterday’s activity to compute token usage, model routing, and costs\n  - Generates a digest and sends via email\n  - Includes privacy guards and a simple user-config interface (no UI needed beyond config in a file)\n- A minimal deployment plan to run this as a small cron/task inside your OpenClaw workspace or container\n\nWould you like me to draft the SKILL.md now and propose a concrete daily-run architecture, or start by confirming the delivery details (address, time, depth)?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":6707,"output":1056,"cacheRead":12544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20307,"cost":{"input":-6707,"output":-1056,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-7763}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772324852515}}
