{"type":"message","id":"414c4d2d","parentId":"aea64c50","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:34:14.042Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to draft a concrete, fixed routing policy. Let me think about what makes sense given their setup:\n\n- They're using OpenClaw with OpenRouter\n- Their default model is `openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex`\n- Current runtime model is `openrouter/openrouter/auto` (which means OpenRouter's auto-routing)\n- They want deterministic, predictable model selection\n- They want to save tokens/costs\n\nLet me also check what's already in place - they have a token-optimizer skill installed. Let me look at that for context on what's already been set up.\n\nLet me draft a clear, actionable routing policy as a SKILL.md or standalone policy document.\n\n\nBefore I write the policy, I should review their current OpenClaw configuration and see what models are actually available through OpenRouter to make sure my recommendations are practical.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_01NHGHSeUopMXKgHzv59kFLF","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/config.yaml 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/config.yml 2>/dev/null || echo \"No config found\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":27403,"output":508,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27911,"cost":{"input":-27403,"output":-508,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-27911}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772325245565}}
