{"type":"message","id":"3e0531ed","parentId":"b5287ab1","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:34:19.372Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_0117BkEkwPTz8j8637KxaeSg","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/config* 2>/dev/null; ls ~/.openclaw/*.json 2>/dev/null; ls ~/.openclaw/*.yaml 2>/dev/null; ls ~/.openclaw/*.yml 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-token-optimizer/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null | head -100"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":27488,"output":137,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27625,"cost":{"input":-27488,"output":-137,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-27625}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772325254223}}
{"type":"message","id":"d37e002b","parentId":"3e0531ed","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:34:19.551Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_0117BkEkwPTz8j8637KxaeSg","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/update-check.json\n---\n---\nname: token-optimizer\ndescription: Reduce OpenClaw token usage and API costs through smart model routing, heartbeat optimization, budget tracking, and native 2026.2.15 features (session pruning, bootstrap size limits, cache TTL alignment). Use when token costs are high, API rate limits are being hit, or hosting multiple agents at scale. The 4 executable scripts (context_optimizer, model_router, heartbeat_optimizer, token_tracker) are local-only — no network requests, no subprocess calls, no system modifications. Reference files (PROVIDERS.md, config-patches.json) document optional multi-provider strategies that require external API keys and network access if you choose to use them. See SECURITY.md for full breakdown.\nversion: 1.4.3\nhomepage: https://github.com/Asif2BD/OpenClaw-Token-Optimizer\nsource: https://github.com/Asif2BD/OpenClaw-Token-Optimizer\nauthor: Asif2BD\nsecurity:\n  verified: true\n  auditor: Oracle (Matrix Zion)\n  audit_date: 2026-02-18\n  scripts_no_network: true\n  scripts_no_code_execution: true\n  scripts_no_subprocess: true\n  scripts_data_local_only: true\n  reference_files_describe_external_services: true\n  optimize_sh_is_convenience_wrapper: true\n  optimize_sh_only_calls_bundled_python_scripts: true\n---\n\n# Token Optimizer\n\nComprehensive toolkit for reducing token usage and API costs in OpenClaw deployments. Combines smart model routing, optimized heartbeat intervals, usage tracking, and multi-provider strategies.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n**Immediate actions** (no config changes needed):\n\n1. **Generate optimized AGENTS.md (BIGGEST WIN!):**\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/context_optimizer.py generate-agents\n   # Creates AGENTS.md.optimized — review and replace your current AGENTS.md\n   ```\n\n2. **Check what context you ACTUALLY need:**\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/context_optimizer.py recommend \"hi, how are you?\"\n   # Shows: Only 2 files needed (not 50+!)\n   ```\n\n3. **Install optimized heartbeat:**\n   ```bash\n   cp assets/HEARTBEAT.template.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n   ```\n\n4. **Enforce cheaper models for casual chat:**\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/model_router.py \"thanks!\"\n   # Single-provider Anthropic setup: Use Sonnet, not Opus\n   # Multi-provider setup (OpenRouter/Together): Use Haiku for max savings\n   ```\n\n5. **Check current token budget:**\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/token_tracker.py check\n   ```\n\n**Expected savings:** 50-80% reduction in token costs for typical workloads (context optimization is the biggest factor!).\n\n## Core Capabilities\n\n### 1. Context Optimization (NEW!)\n\n**Biggest token saver** — Only load files you actually need, not everything upfront.\n\n**Problem:** Default OpenClaw loads ALL context files every session:\n- SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, USER.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md\n- docs/**/*.md (hundreds of files)\n- memory/2026-*.md (daily logs)\n- Total: Often 50K+ tokens before user even speaks!\n\n**Solution:** Lazy loading based on prompt complexity.\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\npython3 scripts/context_optimizer.py recommend \"<user prompt>\"\n```\n\n**Examples:**\n```bash\n# Simple greeting → minimal context (2 files only!)\ncontext_optimizer.py recommend \"hi\"\n→ Load: SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md\n→ Skip: Everything else\n→ Savings: ~80% of context\n\n# Standard work → selective loading\ncontext_optimizer.py recommend \"write a function\"\n→ Load: SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, memory/TODAY.md\n→ Skip: docs, old memory, knowledge base\n→ Savings: ~50% of context\n\n# Complex task → full context\ncontext_optimizer.py recommend \"analyze our entire architecture\"\n→ Load: SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, MEMORY.md, memory/TODAY+YESTERDAY.md\n→ Conditionally load: Relevant docs only\n→ Savings: ~30% of context\n```\n\n**Output format:**"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":169,"aggregated":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/update-check.json\n---\n---\nname: token-optimizer\ndescription: Reduce OpenClaw token usage and API costs through smart model routing, heartbeat optimization, budget tracking, and native 2026.2.15 features (session pruning, bootstrap size limits, cache TTL alignment). Use when token costs are high, API rate limits are being hit, or hosting multiple agents at scale. The 4 executable scripts (context_optimizer, model_router, heartbeat_optimizer, token_tracker) are local-only — no network requests, no subprocess calls, no system modifications. Reference files (PROVIDERS.md, config-patches.json) document optional multi-provider strategies that require external API keys and network access if you choose to use them. See SECURITY.md for full breakdown.\nversion: 1.4.3\nhomepage: https://github.com/Asif2BD/OpenClaw-Token-Optimizer\nsource: https://github.com/Asif2BD/OpenClaw-Token-Optimizer\nauthor: Asif2BD\nsecurity:\n  verified: true\n  auditor: Oracle (Matrix Zion)\n  audit_date: 2026-02-18\n  scripts_no_network: true\n  scripts_no_code_execution: true\n  scripts_no_subprocess: true\n  scripts_data_local_only: true\n  reference_files_describe_external_services: true\n  optimize_sh_is_convenience_wrapper: true\n  optimize_sh_only_calls_bundled_python_scripts: true\n---\n\n# Token Optimizer\n\nComprehensive toolkit for reducing token usage and API costs in OpenClaw deployments. Combines smart model routing, optimized heartbeat intervals, usage tracking, and multi-provider strategies.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n**Immediate actions** (no config changes needed):\n\n1. **Generate optimized AGENTS.md (BIGGEST WIN!):**\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/context_optimizer.py generate-agents\n   # Creates AGENTS.md.optimized — review and replace your current AGENTS.md\n   ```\n\n2. **Check what context you ACTUALLY need:**\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/context_optimizer.py recommend \"hi, how are you?\"\n   # Shows: Only 2 files needed (not 50+!)\n   ```\n\n3. **Install optimized heartbeat:**\n   ```bash\n   cp assets/HEARTBEAT.template.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n   ```\n\n4. **Enforce cheaper models for casual chat:**\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/model_router.py \"thanks!\"\n   # Single-provider Anthropic setup: Use Sonnet, not Opus\n   # Multi-provider setup (OpenRouter/Together): Use Haiku for max savings\n   ```\n\n5. **Check current token budget:**\n   ```bash\n   python3 scripts/token_tracker.py check\n   ```\n\n**Expected savings:** 50-80% reduction in token costs for typical workloads (context optimization is the biggest factor!).\n\n## Core Capabilities\n\n### 1. Context Optimization (NEW!)\n\n**Biggest token saver** — Only load files you actually need, not everything upfront.\n\n**Problem:** Default OpenClaw loads ALL context files every session:\n- SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, USER.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md\n- docs/**/*.md (hundreds of files)\n- memory/2026-*.md (daily logs)\n- Total: Often 50K+ tokens before user even speaks!\n\n**Solution:** Lazy loading based on prompt complexity.\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\npython3 scripts/context_optimizer.py recommend \"<user prompt>\"\n```\n\n**Examples:**\n```bash\n# Simple greeting → minimal context (2 files only!)\ncontext_optimizer.py recommend \"hi\"\n→ Load: SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md\n→ Skip: Everything else\n→ Savings: ~80% of context\n\n# Standard work → selective loading\ncontext_optimizer.py recommend \"write a function\"\n→ Load: SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, memory/TODAY.md\n→ Skip: docs, old memory, knowledge base\n→ Savings: ~50% of context\n\n# Complex task → full context\ncontext_optimizer.py recommend \"analyze our entire architecture\"\n→ Load: SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, MEMORY.md, memory/TODAY+YESTERDAY.md\n→ Conditionally load: Relevant docs only\n→ Savings: ~30% of context\n```\n\n**Output format:**","cwd":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772325259546}}
{"type":"message","id":"96593d35","parentId":"d37e002b","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:34:28.118Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Drafting routing policy**\n\nI need to draft the policy in a SKILL.md style and create a concrete fixed routing policy along with a deterministic logging plan. I’ll outline the content of the SKILL.md. There shouldn't be any tool calls. I’ll structure the policy with clear sections including Overview, Scope, Model Ladder, Trigger Rules, Caching, and others. Finally, I’ll ask for confirmation on the details to ensure everything is correct before delivering the drafted OpenCopilotRoutingPolicy_SKILL.md content.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\nHere’s a concrete, fixed routing policy you can review and implement as an OpenClaw SKILL.md-style document. It’s designed to be deterministic, reproducible, and fully auditable.\n\nOpenCopilot Pro - Deterministic Model Routing Policy (SKILL.md)\n\n1) Purpose\n- Provide a fixed, transparent model-routing policy to minimize token usage while preserving answer quality.\n- Ensure all decisions are logged with rationale for auditability.\n\n2) Scope\n- Applies to all user prompts routed through the OpenRouter/OpenCopilot subsystem unless explicitly overridden by a user-facing toggle (e.g., force-high-power, disable web).\n\n3) Model ladder (cost/quality tiers)\n- Tier 1 (Cheap): small/low-cost model (e.g., drafting, summaries, simple classification)\n- Tier 2 (Medium): mid-range model for moderate reasoning, multi-step tasks, moderate context\n- Tier 3 (Expensive): high-power model for complex reasoning, code tasks, long-context analysis, or when high accuracy is required\n- Optional: local/private model if configured (treated as Tier 0 in policy)\n\n4) Fixed routing rules (deterministic decision tree)\n- Rule A: If the prompt is a simple, self-contained request and requires minimal reasoning or no external data, route to Tier 1.\n  - Examples: greetings, quick summaries, straightforward factual lookups with minimal context.\n- Rule B: If the prompt requires some reasoning, planning, or combination of small context plus a few steps, route to Tier 2.\n  - Examples: drafting code snippets, moderate analysis, structured outlines, moderate-context planning.\n- Rule C: If the prompt requires deep reasoning, multi-step logic, large context, or verification against external data, route to Tier 3.\n  - Examples: architecture analysis, complex debugging, long-form content generation with constraints, multi-document synthesis.\n- Rule D: If the user has a forced-model preference, honor it:\n  - Force-Tier-1/2/3 overrides A–C.\n  - If “disable web” is set, do not spawn web-enabled tasks even if needed to answer.\n- Rule E: If the prompt matches a previously cached solution within the last N minutes (configurable, default 60 minutes), reuse the cached Tier and output.\n- Rule F: If a lower tier results in unsatisfactory results (as indicated by a structured success/failure flag in the response), optionally re-run with the next higher tier for refinement (no automatic looping beyond Tier 3).\n\n5) Context and prompt handling\n- Context window: use only the minimal required files and data per the context optimizer rules. Do not preload full memory/docs unless required by the prompt.\n- Prompt normalization: deterministically trim whitespace, standardize casing where appropriate, and map known synonyms to canonical intents before routing.\n\n6) Caching and reuse\n- Cache the following for quick reuse: prompt hash, selected Tier, key rationale, and the produced output (subject to privacy).\n- If the same prompt (or near-identical prompt) appears within the cache window, reuse the prior Tier and summary where appropriate.\n\n7) Web and tools handling\n- Web access: only if needed to answer and if allowed by the user settings.\n- If web is allowed and required, route to Tier 3 for authoritative results or Tier 2 if the data can be sufficiently sourced from internal knowledge plus cached knowledge.\n- Tools (code execution, search, etc.) should be gated behind tier and necessity; avoid unnecessary tool calls to save tokens.\n\n8) Logging schema (deterministic audit trail)\nEach invocation logs:\n- timestamp (UTC)\n- prompt_hash (hash of standardized prompt)\n- chosen_tier (Tier 1 / Tier 2 / Tier 3)\n- rationale_tag (e.g., “RuleA-basic”, “RuleB-planning”, “RuleC-architecture”, “cached”, “force-tier-2”)\n- context_used (summary or list of files loaded)\n- web_used (true/false)\n- tools_used (list)\n- tokens_estimated (approximate tokens for this call)\n- output_summary (one-line descriptor of result)\n- user-visible_mode (normal / draft / verbose)\n- any caveats or next-step recommendations\n\n9) Privacy guardrails\n- Do not persist raw prompts beyond what’s necessary for the digest or audit trail.\n- If data retention companions exist, ensure they are optional and configurable.\n- Provide a per-session toggle to suppress detailed logs (only high-level rationale remains).\n\n10) Fail-safes and overrides\n- If Tier 1 fails to produce a usable answer, escalate to Tier 2; if Tier 2 fails, escalate to Tier 3.\n- If an unexpected error occurs, fall back to Tier 1 for user-friendliness and show a brief error note with recommended next steps.\n\n11) Configuration knobs (defaults; easy to override per-user)\n- routing_policy: fixed (values: A/B/C) or explicit per-prompt (apply Rule A/B/C)\n- force_tier: 0 (none) | 1 | 2 | 3\n- enable_web: true/false\n- cache_ttl_minutes: 60\n- log_detail_level: minimal / standard / verbose\n- context_quiet_mode: true/false\n\n12) Example workflows (for clarity)\n- Simple prompt: \"Summarize the latest meeting.\" → Tier 1, minimal context, return concise summary.\n- Code task: \"Refactor this function\" with a moderate length snippet → Tier 2, produce outline and refactor suggestions.\n- Architecture analysis: “Evaluate the system architecture for scalability and cost” → Tier 3, multi-document synthesis, external data if needed.\n\n13) Deliverables for review\n- Draft SKILL.md with the above policy encoded in markdown, including:\n  - Purpose and scope\n  - Detailed routing table (Rule A–C)\n  - Caching and logging schema\n  - Privacy guardrails\n  - Configuration knobs (with defaults)\n  - Example prompts and expected tier assignments\n  - Testing plan (deterministic test prompts and expected tier outcomes)\n\n14) Next steps\n- I can produce the actual SKILL.md text now for you to review.\n- If you want, I’ll also draft a small set of controlled test prompts (a test suite) to verify deterministic routing on your side.\n\nWould you like me to generate the finalized SKILL.md text right away, or would you prefer I tailor the policy to any specific model lineup you have configured (e.g., exact tier names or model names you’re using in OpenRouter)?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":9526,"output":1555,"cacheRead":13056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24137,"cost":{"input":-9526,"output":-1555,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-11081}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772325259551}}
{"type":"message","id":"4073a44a","parentId":"96593d35","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:39:41.864Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"generate the finalized skill.md and I'd like a daily report emailed to me on token usage"}],"timestamp":1772325581861}}
{"type":"message","id":"75332e47","parentId":"4073a44a","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:39:46.962Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_write_ZbItN2sRfUPvjzLy5RTZ","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# SKILL.md - OpenCopilot Daily Intelligence & Token Optimizer\n\n## Purpose\nA deterministic routing, budget tracking, and automated reporting skill to reduce token costs while providing daily oversight of AI operations.\n\n## Capabilities\n\n### 1. Deterministic Model Routing\nRoutes prompts based on complexity to minimize cost:\n- **TIER 1 (Haiku/Flash):** Casual chat, greetings, status checks, and simple summaries (< 2k context).\n- **TIER 2 (Sonnet/GPT-4o):** Coding, technical analysis, multi-step logic, and moderate research.\n- **TIER 3 (Opus/O1):** High-stakes architecture, deep reasoning, or when Tier 2 fails.\n\n### 2. Context Pruning\nBefore every request, runs `context_optimizer.py` to ensure only the necessary files are loaded (SOUL.md and IDENTITY.md by default; others only on-demand).\n\n### 3. Daily Intelligence Email\nSends a summary every morning at 07:00 AM (local) containing:\n- **Usage Stats:** Total tokens/cost for the last 24 hours.\n- **Efficiency Grade:** % of requests successfully handled by Tier 1 vs Tier 3.\n- **Key Actions:** Summary of what was accomplished.\n- **Save Tips:** Recommendations on how to prune more context or use cheaper models.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Manual Trigger\n`openclaw copilot status` - Shows current daily usage and projected monthly spend.\n`openclaw copilot report` - Manually triggers the daily intelligence email for testing.\n\n### Automated Sequence (via Cron)\nThe system runs `scripts/generate_daily_report.py` at 07:00 AM to send the email.\n\n## Configuration\nEdit `config/copilot-pro.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"USER_EMAIL_HERE\",\n  \"report_time\": \"07:00\",\n  \"budget_monthly_usd\": 20.00,\n  \"default_tier\": \"tier-1\",\n  \"routing_rules\": \"deterministic-v1\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n*Note: This skill integrates directly with the token-optimizer skill scripts.*\n","file_path":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/SKILL.md"},"thoughtSignature":"{\"index\":0,\"id\":\"tool_write_ZbItN2sRfUPvjzLy5RTZ\",\"type\":\"reasoning.encrypted\",\"data\":\"CiEBjz1rX5XR0xCnPT67y7gudbKWxn0eXrYLWic8wLmKHmQ=\",\"format\":\"google-gemini-v1\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":24774,"output":521,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25295,"cost":{"input":-24774,"output":-521,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-25295}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772325581863}}
