{"type":"message","id":"5e6153ae","parentId":"54d0b975","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:39:49.041Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_tI3kuaug0gZTM0EQav7UNaOn","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SKILL.md - OpenCopilot Daily Intelligence & Token Optimizer\n\n## Purpose\nA deterministic routing, budget tracking, and automated reporting skill to reduce token costs while providing daily oversight of AI operations.\n\n## Capabilities\n\n### 1. Deterministic Model Routing\nRoutes prompts based on complexity to minimize cost:\n- **TIER 1 (Haiku/Flash):** Casual chat, greetings, status checks, and simple summaries (< 2k context).\n- **TIER 2 (Sonnet/GPT-4o):** Coding, technical analysis, multi-step logic, and moderate research.\n- **TIER 3 (Opus/O1):** High-stakes architecture, deep reasoning, or when Tier 2 fails.\n\n### 2. Context Pruning\nBefore every request, runs `context_optimizer.py` to ensure only the necessary files are loaded (SOUL.md and IDENTITY.md by default; others only on-demand).\n\n### 3. Daily Intelligence Email\nSends a summary every morning at 07:00 AM (local) containing:\n- **Usage Stats:** Total tokens/cost for the last 24 hours.\n- **Efficiency Grade:** % of requests successfully handled by Tier 1 vs Tier 3.\n- **Key Actions:** Summary of what was accomplished.\n- **Save Tips:** Recommendations on how to prune more context or use cheaper models.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Manual Trigger\n`openclaw copilot status` - Shows current daily usage and projected monthly spend.\n`openclaw copilot report` - Manually triggers the daily intelligence email for testing.\n\n### Automated Sequence (via Cron)\nThe system runs `scripts/generate_daily_report.py` at 07:00 AM to send the email.\n\n## Configuration\nEdit `config/copilot-pro.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"USER_EMAIL_HERE\",\n  \"report_time\": \"07:00\",\n  \"budget_monthly_usd\": 20.00,\n  \"default_tier\": \"tier-1\",\n  \"routing_rules\": \"deterministic-v1\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n*Note: This skill integrates directly with the token-optimizer skill scripts.*"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":398,"aggregated":"# SKILL.md - OpenCopilot Daily Intelligence & Token Optimizer\n\n## Purpose\nA deterministic routing, budget tracking, and automated reporting skill to reduce token costs while providing daily oversight of AI operations.\n\n## Capabilities\n\n### 1. Deterministic Model Routing\nRoutes prompts based on complexity to minimize cost:\n- **TIER 1 (Haiku/Flash):** Casual chat, greetings, status checks, and simple summaries (< 2k context).\n- **TIER 2 (Sonnet/GPT-4o):** Coding, technical analysis, multi-step logic, and moderate research.\n- **TIER 3 (Opus/O1):** High-stakes architecture, deep reasoning, or when Tier 2 fails.\n\n### 2. Context Pruning\nBefore every request, runs `context_optimizer.py` to ensure only the necessary files are loaded (SOUL.md and IDENTITY.md by default; others only on-demand).\n\n### 3. Daily Intelligence Email\nSends a summary every morning at 07:00 AM (local) containing:\n- **Usage Stats:** Total tokens/cost for the last 24 hours.\n- **Efficiency Grade:** % of requests successfully handled by Tier 1 vs Tier 3.\n- **Key Actions:** Summary of what was accomplished.\n- **Save Tips:** Recommendations on how to prune more context or use cheaper models.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Manual Trigger\n`openclaw copilot status` - Shows current daily usage and projected monthly spend.\n`openclaw copilot report` - Manually triggers the daily intelligence email for testing.\n\n### Automated Sequence (via Cron)\nThe system runs `scripts/generate_daily_report.py` at 07:00 AM to send the email.\n\n## Configuration\nEdit `config/copilot-pro.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"USER_EMAIL_HERE\",\n  \"report_time\": \"07:00\",\n  \"budget_monthly_usd\": 20.00,\n  \"default_tier\": \"tier-1\",\n  \"routing_rules\": \"deterministic-v1\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n*Note: This skill integrates directly with the token-optimizer skill scripts.*","cwd":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772325589037}}
{"type":"message","id":"c7c40d6f","parentId":"5e6153ae","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:40:17.494Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me build the routing policy, the report generator script, and the config:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_01J4LPUa1tMfLiTaEndf2poa","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Deterministic Model Routing Policy v1\n\n## Decision Tree\n\nEvery inbound prompt is classified by a single pass through these rules, in order.\nThe FIRST matching rule wins. No ambiguity, no randomness.\n\n### Rule A → TIER 1 (Cheapest)\nConditions (ALL must be true):\n- Prompt length < 200 tokens (after normalization)\n- No code blocks or technical markers\n- No multi-step indicators (\"then\", \"after that\", \"next\", \"also\")\n- No external data needed (no URLs, no \"search for\", no \"find me\")\n- Intent is one of: greeting, acknowledgment, yes/no answer, simple factual lookup, status check, thank you\n\nExamples:\n- \"hey\"\n- \"thanks\"\n- \"what time is it?\"\n- \"yes do that\"\n- \"how's the weather?\"\n\nModel: anthropic/claude-haiku-4 or google/gemini-flash\n\n### Rule B → TIER 2 (Mid-range)\nConditions (ANY is true, and Rule A did not match):\n- Prompt length 200–2000 tokens\n- Contains code blocks or technical terms\n- Requires 2–5 reasoning steps\n- Needs file reading, editing, or moderate context\n- Research task with a known scope (single topic, bounded)\n\nExamples:\n- \"refactor this function to use async/await\"\n- \"draft an email to my team about the outage\"\n- \"summarize yesterday's activity\"\n- \"what does this error mean?\" + stack trace\n\nModel: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4 or openai/gpt-4o\n\n### Rule C → TIER 3 (Most Capable)\nConditions (ANY is true, and Rules A/B did not match):\n- Prompt length > 2000 tokens\n- Requires deep multi-step reasoning (>5 steps)\n- Architecture, design, or strategy analysis\n- Multi-document synthesis\n- Tier 2 produced an unsatisfactory result (escalation)\n- User explicitly requests high-power mode\n\nExamples:\n- \"evaluate our entire system architecture for scalability\"\n- \"analyze these 3 documents and produce a comparison matrix\"\n- \"debug this complex race condition across 4 files\"\n\nModel: anthropic/claude-opus-4 or openai/o1\n\n### Rule D → USER OVERRIDE\nIf the user sets `force_tier: 1|2|3` in config or says \"use tier X\", honor it unconditionally.\n\n### Rule E → CACHE HIT\nIf the same prompt hash was seen in the last `cache_ttl_minutes` (default 60):\n- Reuse the prior tier assignment and output summary\n- Log as rationale_tag: \"cached\"\n\n### Rule F → ESCALATION\nIf a lower tier returns a structured failure flag:\n- Escalate exactly one tier (1→2, 2→3)\n- Never loop: if Tier 3 fails, return error with recommendations\n- Log escalation with rationale_tag: \"escalation-from-tier-X\"\n\n## Logging Schema\n\nEvery call produces a log entry:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"timestamp\": \"2025-07-15T12:00:00Z\",\n  \"prompt_hash\": \"sha256:abc123...\",\n  \"prompt_length_tokens\": 142,\n  \"chosen_tier\": 1,\n  \"rationale_tag\": \"RuleA-greeting\",\n  \"model_used\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4\",\n  \"context_files_loaded\": [\"SOUL.md\", \"IDENTITY.md\"],\n  \"web_used\": false,\n  \"tools_used\": [],\n  \"tokens_input\": 450,\n  \"tokens_output\": 120,\n  \"cost_usd\": 0.0003,\n  \"escalated\": false,\n  \"cached\": false\n}\n```\n\n## Context Loading Policy\n\n| Tier | Always Load | Conditionally Load | Never Load |\n|------|------------|-------------------|------------|\n| 1    | SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md | — | Everything else |\n| 2    | SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, memory/TODAY.md | TOOLS.md (if tools mentioned), USER.md (if personal) | Old memory, docs, knowledge |\n| 3    | SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, MEMORY.md, memory/TODAY.md | Relevant docs, knowledge files | Unrelated docs |\n\n## Web & Tools Gating\n\n| Tier | Web Allowed | Tools Allowed |\n|------|------------|--------------|\n| 1    | No         | No           |\n| 2    | If needed  | File read/edit, exec |\n| 3    | Yes        | All          |\n\n## Budget Guardrails\n\n- If daily spend exceeds 80% of `budget_monthly_usd / 30`, downgrade all Tier 3 calls to Tier 2 for remainder of day\n- If daily spend exceeds 95%, downgrade everything to Tier 1 (emergency mode)\n- Log budget warnings in daily report\n\n## Privacy\n\n- Prompt hashes stored, not raw prompts (unless user opts in via `log_detail_level: verbose`)\n- Logs auto-purge after 30 days (configurable)\n- No data leaves the local environment unless explicitly triggered (email send, web fetch)\n","file_path":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/ROUTING_POLICY.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":31817,"output":1377,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33194,"cost":{"input":-31817,"output":-1377,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-33194}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772325589041}}
