nt docs, knowledge files | Unrelated docs |\n\n## Web & Tools Gating\n\n| Tier | Web Allowed | Tools Allowed |\n|------|------------|--------------|\n| 1    | No         | No           |\n| 2    | If needed  | File read/edit, exec |\n| 3    | Yes        | All          |\n\n## Budget Guardrails\n\n- If daily spend exceeds 80% of `budget_monthly_usd / 30`, downgrade all Tier 3 calls to Tier 2 for remainder of day\n- If daily spend exceeds 95%, downgrade everything to Tier 1 (emergency mode)\n- Log budget warnings in daily report\n\n## Privacy\n\n- Prompt hashes stored, not raw prompts (unless user opts in via `log_detail_level: verbose`)\n- Logs auto-purge after 30 days (configurable)\n- No data leaves the local environment unless explicitly triggered (email send, web fetch)","cwd":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772325619311}}
{"type":"message","id":"abeb8707","parentId":"d96f58bc","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:40:23.114Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me build the daily report generator and config. I need to check what email setup you have:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_01GDN1FPL4B2EMLAb3NaXN4y","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/gmail/SKILL.md","limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":34609,"output":110,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34719,"cost":{"input":-34609,"output":-110,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-34719}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772325619315}}
{"type":"message","id":"376e6020","parentId":"abeb8707","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:40:23.128Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01GDN1FPL4B2EMLAb3NaXN4y","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: gmail\ndescription: |\n  Gmail API integration with managed OAuth. Read, send, and manage emails, threads, labels, and drafts. Use this skill when users want to interact with Gmail. For other third party apps, use the api-gateway skill (https://clawhub.ai/byungkyu/api-gateway).\ncompatibility: Requires network access and valid Maton API key\nmetadata:\n  author: maton\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  clawdbot:\n    emoji: 🧠\n    requires:\n      env:\n        - MATON_API_KEY\n---\n\n# Gmail\n\nAccess the Gmail API with managed OAuth authentication. Read, send, and manage emails, threads, labels, and drafts.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# List messages\npython <<'EOF'\nimport urllib.request, os, json\nreq = urllib.request.Request('https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?maxResults=10')\nreq.add_header('Authorization', f'Bearer {os.environ[\"MATON_API_KEY\"]}')\nprint(json.dumps(json.load(urllib.request.urlopen(req)), indent=2))\nEOF\n```\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttps://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/{native-api-path}\n```\n\nReplace `{native-api-path}` with the actual Gmail API endpoint path. The gateway proxies requests to `gmail.googleapis.com` and automatically injects your OAuth token.\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll requests require the Maton API key in the Authorization header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer $MATON_API_KEY\n```\n\n**Environment Variable:** Set your API key as `MATON_API_KEY`:\n\n```bash\n\n[290 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772325623122}}
