{"type":"message","id":"dc430e24","parentId":"4cd6246d","timestamp":"2026-03-01T00:40:36.616Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] I’ve generated and saved the finalized OpenCopilot Daily Intelligence & Token Optimizer policy and wired up the routing policy draft. Here’s what’s ready and where to find it:\n\nWhat I did\n- Created and saved OpenCopilot Daily Intelligence & Token Optimizer SKILL.md\n  - Path: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/SKILL.md\n  - Content: defines daily email reporting, token-budget awareness, and MVP scope for a personal copilot with token-conscious behavior.\n- Created the deterministic routing policy document\n  - Path: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/ROUTING_POLICY.md\n  - Content: detailed Rule A/B/C (Tier 1/2/3), cache, escalation, logging schema, context rules, web/tool gating, and privacy guardrails.\n- Drafted a concrete wiring for a daily digest, and included a minimal config example in the SKILL.md (email delivery, time, budget, etc.)\n- You also have an existing baseline SKILL for the Gmail integration and token optimizer in your workspace, plus a structure to hook up daily digest generation script (generate_daily_report.py) to cron.\n\nWhat you now have to review\n- OpenCopilot Daily Intelligence & Token Optimizer\n  - SKILL.md: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/SKILL.md\n  - ROUTING_POLICY.md: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/ROUTING_POLICY.md\n\nKey features in the policy\n- Deterministic model routing (Tier 1/2/3) with explicit rules A/B/C\n- Context pruning before each request\n- Daily intelligence email with token usage, efficiency, and save-tips\n- Structured logging schema for auditability\n- Context loading, web/tools gating, and budget guardrails\n- Privacy safeguards and clear configuration knobs\n\nWhat I need from you to move forward\n- Delivery details for the daily email digest:\n  - Email address to send to (the Gmail pipeline you mentioned)\n  - Preferred daily digest time (default 07:00 local)\n  - Depth of detail in the digest (high-level vs. full prompts vs. verbose logs)\n- Any adjustments to the routing policy (model names, tier names, or exact models you want aligned with your setup)\n- Confirm whether you want the daily digest to include:\n  - Tokens input/output and cost estimates (yes/no)\n  - Efficiency grade (Tier 1 vs Tier 3 ratio)\n  - Attachments (CSV/Markdown) versus inline body content only\n\nNext steps I can take\n- Generate a finalized, publication-ready SKILL.md and a test suite of deterministic prompts to validate routing.\n- Add a concrete daily_report generator script (generate_daily_report.py) wired to your Gmail pipeline, with:\n  - Reading yesterday’s activity\n  - Computing tokens, cost, tier usage\n  - Composing a digest (plain text and optional HTML)\n  - Sending via email at the configured time\n- If you want, I can also draft a minimal deployment plan to run this as a cron job in a container or your OpenClaw workspace.\n\nWould you like me to proceed with:\n- Generating a finalized, polished SKILL.md text right away, and a small test prompt suite to validate routing, and\n- Drafting the daily_report.py script and wiring it to your Gmail pipeline with a sample config block?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":1694,"output":1049,"cacheRead":26368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29111,"cost":{"input":-1694,"output":-1049,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-2743}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772325626527}}
