{"type":"message","id":"2cac402b","parentId":"e0dadb68","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:03:42.243Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Explaining proactive behavior**\n\nI want to keep my response concise and focus on explaining the difference between proactive behavior and monitoring. I'll describe what the OpenCopilot Pro plan includes: things like deterministic routing, token budgeting, proactive suggestions, auto-adjusting model choices, caching, and alerts.\n\nThen, I’ll lay out the options the user has between passive monitoring and proactive automation, and finally, I should ask for their preference. Using bullet points might help with clarity here!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Short answer: it can be both a monitor and progressively proactive.\n\nWhat you’ve got now\n- The daily digest is primarily a visibility tool (monitor): it reports usage, cost, and tier distribution after the fact.\n- It also documents routing decisions (logging) so you can audit what model tier was used.\n\nHow we can make it pro-active\n- Automatic model routing: enforce the fixed policy (Tier 1/2/3) in real time, choosing the cheapest tier that meets the task, with explicit fallbacks when needed.\n- Smart budget control: nudge down to Tier 1 when you’re high on daily spend; escalate only when necessary.\n- Context-aware shortcuts: cache common prompts, reuse prior summaries, and avoid web/tool calls unless required.\n- Proactive suggestions: after a session, surface tips to save tokens (e.g., rephrase prompts, shorten context, use drafts, enable caching).\n- Alerts and autoscalers: notify you if a task consistently hits Tier 3 or if budget alarms trigger, and offer auto-adjust options.\n\nWhat I need to know to tailor it\n- Do you want strict automatic routing with no manual overrides, or keep a “force tier” override available per session?\n- How aggressive should budget-driven downgrades be? (e.g., downgrade Tier 3 to Tier 2 at 60% of daily budget, or only at 90%)\n- Should I generate a per-session routing rationale in the log for full auditability, or keep it lean?\n- Any tasks you want explicitly protected from downgrades (e.g., code reviews, critical decisions)?\n\nIf you want, I can convert the policy into a concrete, enforceable openclaw skill (SKILL.md) with explicit rules, and a small module to emit proactive suggestions and alerts."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":33437,"output":571,"cacheRead":2944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36952,"cost":{"input":-33437,"output":-571,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-34008}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772327016489}}
