{"type":"message","id":"06522fba","parentId":"a6c950a8","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:08:44.072Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Proposing policy adjustments**\n\nI think we should implement a plan for adjusting our response policy. I’d define a low aggressiveness with a force tier override, propose keeping default at Tier 1, only allowing Tier 2 for coding prompts, and turning off Tier 3 by default. I’ll outline changes in SKILL.md and logging, and we need confirmation before updating the routing policy and the config. It sounds good to provide a concise summary and suggest these updates for approval!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Thanks. I’ll keep it lean and make the force-tier override available.\n\nPlanned changes\n- Force tier override: add a per-session switch (force_tier: 1|2|3) that, when set, ignores normal routing and uses the chosen tier. Default is no force (null).\n- Aggressiveness: keep Tier 2/Tier 3 usage minimal:\n  - Default routing: Tier 1 for simple prompts; Tier 2 only for clearly scoped, non-critical tasks (coding, moderate reasoning) and only if the prompt clearly warrants it.\n  - Tier 3: disabled by default for non-critical usage; available only via explicit user toggle.\n- Policy simplification: Rules A/B kept strict; Tier 3 paths exist but are rarely hit unless forced or if a prompt clearly requires deep reasoning.\n- Logging: lean but auditable per-session routing rationale and the final tier used (with force-tier visible when applied).\n\nWhat I’ll update\n- ROUTING_POLICY.md: add explicit note that Tier 3 is off by default and can be overridden by force_tier.\n- COPILOT config: expose an optional field like \"force_tier\": null|1|2|3, and set default to null.\n- SKILL.md (OpenCopilot Pro): reflect the presence of a lean mode and the force-tier override, plus a simple per-session rationale.\n- Daily digest: keep high-level content, but include a simple line if a force tier was used.\n\nQuestions to lock in\n- Do you want Tier 2 occasionally permitted only for specific tasks (e.g., coding help) via keyword triggers, or strictly manual override?\n- Should the force_tier appear in the daily log as “force-tier X” when used?\n- Is it acceptable to keep Tier 3 fully off unless you explicitly enable it later?\n\nIf you’re happy with this plan, I’ll implement the changes to ROUTING_POLICY.md, update the config schema, and draft the corresponding SKILL.md edits."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":36977,"output":701,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37678,"cost":{"input":-36977,"output":-701,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-37678}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772327317064}}
