{"type":"message","id":"167e1d05","parentId":"97e3f4a0","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:13:04.620Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Confirming updates and next steps**\n\nI need to confirm the updates I've made and outline the next steps. The user asked me to remember something earlier, and I’ve implemented changes like the lean routing policy and force_tier. I'll provide a brief summary and ask the user to confirm tests, while reminding them about the test preview option.\n\nI should also mention that I updated the ROUTING_POLICY.md, COPILOT config, and the daily reporting script. Finally, I'll offer to run a test preview if they'd like. Keeping this concise!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"All set. I’ve implemented your lean OpenCopilot plan and saved the key settings.\n\nWhat I updated\n- Routing policy: ROUTING_POLICY.md upgraded to Lean v2\n  - Tier 1 default; Tier 2 triggered only by keyword cues\n  - Tier 3 disabled by default (only enabled via force_tier)\n  - Force tier override available per session (but not surfaced in the digest)\n  - Guardrails to minimize tool calls\n- Config: copilot-pro.json updated\n  - email: austin.king@parallon.com\n  - report_time: 08:30\n  - budget_monthly_usd: 20.00\n  - default_tier: tier-1\n  - routing_rules: deterministic-v1\n  - digest_depth: high-level\n  - attachment_format: markdown\n  - drilldown: true\n- Daily digest tooling: added lean daily report scaffolding\n  - DAILY_REPORT.py skeleton and generate_daily_report.py script wired\n  - Output reports saved under /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/reports/\n  - Test run showed sample digest/detailed reports generated\n\nWhat this means for you\n- The daily digest at 08:30 will be high-level with a drill-down Markdown attachment.\n- The model routing is deterministic and lean by default; Tier 2 is only used for clearly scoped, keyword-triggered tasks; Tier 3 is off unless you explicitly enable it via force_tier.\n- Tool calls are minimized by design; only needed prompts will trigger tools.\n- You can still override per session with a force_tier (1/2/3) if you ever want to test non-default behavior.\n\nNext steps\n- If you want, I can run a test digest now to email you a preview, or wait for tomorrow’s 08:30 digest.\n- Want me to enable a one-time test email to your work address to verify formatting and attachments?\n- If you later want to adjust the exact keyword triggers for Tier 2, I can tune ROUTING_POLICY.md accordingly.\n\nWould you like a quick test digest emailed to you now, or should we wait for the live 08:30 digest?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":37662,"output":625,"cacheRead":1536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39823,"cost":{"input":-37662,"output":-625,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-38287}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772327579460}}
