{"type":"message","id":"03e15df7","parentId":"f471d9f1","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:18:27.552Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Configuring fallback models**\n\nI need to respond concisely to the user's request about using fallback models without OpenRouter. I should propose steps for configuring local or alternative providers, adjusting the routing policy. Specifically, I can suggest creating a fallback chain with a Tier 1 local model and a Tier 2 external non-OpenRouter model. I should also confirm there won't be any testing involved and offer updates, like adding a \"fallback_model\" path and ensuring logs show any fallback usage. Clarifying which non-OpenRouter options are preferred will be helpful too.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it—no test. And we can definitely add non-OpenRouter fallbacks.\n\nWhat I can configure now\n- Add a non-OpenRouter fallback path: when the lean routing can’t satisfy a request or when you explicitly want to avoid OpenRouter, route Tier 1/2 tasks to a local or alternate provider, and only use OpenRouter for the highest-need tasks.\n- Example fallback options:\n  - Local/private model: run a lightweight on-device or local-LLM (e.g., a small open-source model you host).\n  - Alternative cloud provider: pivot Tier 1/2 to a different API (not OpenRouter) if you have keys (e.g., a separate GPT/LLM tier).\n  - Cache-first path: rely on cached results for repeat prompts before hitting any external service.\n- Logging: clearly log when a fallback was used and which provider/model was chosen, while keeping the digest lean.\n\nWhat I need from you to implement\n- Which non-OpenRouter path do you want as the default fallback?\n  - Option A: local/private model (on your box or a small VM)\n  - Option B: alternative cloud provider with its API key\n  - Option C: purely cached results with no external calls (until first run)\n- If you have a specific local model or alternate provider, share the model name or API endpoint and any auth details you’re comfortable storing in the config.\n- Should fallbacks be allowed for Tier 1 as well, or only for Tier 2 when OpenRouter would otherwise be used?\n- Any security/privacy constraints for using a non-OpenRouter path (data leaving your environment, retention, etc.)?\n\nProposed next steps (fast path)\n1) Add a ROUTING_POLICY update that includes a “fallback” branch:\n   - If OpenRouter path would be used but you’ve enabled fallback, route Tier 1/2 to the chosen non-OpenRouter provider.\n   - Tier 3 remains disabled by default; available only if you enable it along with a non-OpenRouter path.\n2) Extend configCopilot.json with:\n   - fallback_provider: null | local_llm | alt_provider_name\n   - fallback_settings: endpoint/keys if needed\n3) Update logs to include a “fallback_used” flag and “fallback_provider” field (for audit without leaking sensitive prompts).\n4) Keep the daily digest as-is; add a short line noting if a fallback was used for any task in the day.\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Add a concrete fallback path option (identify which path you want), and\n- Update ROUTING_POLICY.md and the config accordingly so we can test the behavior without OpenRouter?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":38050,"output":979,"cacheRead":1792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40821,"cost":{"input":-38050,"output":-979,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-39029}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772327901247}}
