{"type":"message","id":"6eef612e","parentId":"cf4dc561","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:29:07.382Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it. You have two other rate-limited but free providers that we can treat as primary or fallback options to save budget.\n\nHere's the plan:\n1.  **Prioritize Free Providers:** Update the routing policy to attempt your free/rate-limited providers first for Tier 1 and Tier 2 tasks.\n2.  **Fallback to Paid:** Use OpenRouter only as a spillover when the free providers are rate-limited or fail.\n3.  **Config Update:** I need to know which providers these are (e.g., Google Gemini free tier, Groq, HuggingFace, etc.) to configure the client correctly.\n\n**Action:**\nI will update `ROUTING_POLICY.md` to reflect this \"Free-First\" strategy and ask you for the provider details to update the config.\n\n**Q:** What are the names of the two free providers you use? (e.g., Gemini, Groq, Cohere, etc.)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":40090,"output":205,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40295,"cost":{"input":-40090,"output":-205,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-40295}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772328542312}}
