{"type":"message","id":"7ad9d093","parentId":"53f4a862","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:31:00.659Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_YZRMB7riSzFcI9xXBDAbUjCH","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/ROUTING_POLICY.md","content":"# Deterministic Model Routing Policy v2 (Lean with Free-First Fallbacks)\n\n## Principles\n- Default to Tier 1 (cheapest) for everything.\n- Tier 2 only when specific keyword triggers are detected.\n- Tier 3 is OFF unless explicitly enabled by the user.\n- Minimize tool calls: only invoke tools when the prompt cannot be answered from memory/context alone.\n- Force-tier override available per session but not logged in the daily digest\n- Free-first: try free providers first for Tier 1/2; spillover to OpenRouter for Tier 3 or when free providers are rate-limited or fail.\n\n## Decision Tree\n\nEvery inbound prompt is classified by a single pass. First match wins.\n\n### Rule A → TIER 1 (Default — Cheapest)\nUse for ALL prompts unless Rule B explicitly triggers.\n\nModel selection order:\n- Free providers prioritized: google-gemini-pro-3.1-preview, gpt-5.3-codex\n- If free providers unavailable or rate-limited, spillover to paid OpenRouter Tier 1 path\n\nModel: google-gemini-pro-3.1-preview\n\n### Rule B → TIER 2 (Keyword-Triggered Only)\nConditions — prompt contains ONE OR MORE of these triggers:\n- Code keywords: \"refactor\", \"debug\", \"function\", \"script\", \"code review\", \"write code\", \"fix this code\"\n- Analysis keywords: \"compare\", \"analyze\", \"evaluate\", \"design\", \"architect\"\n- Multi-step keywords: \"step by step\", \"walk me through\", \"break down\"\n- Research keywords: \"research\", \"deep dive\", \"comprehensive\"\n\nIf NO keyword triggers match → stays Tier 1.\n\nModel: google-gemini-pro-3.1-preview (Tier 2 path via free provider)\n\n### Rule C → TIER 3 (DISABLED by default)\nOnly activates when:\n- User explicitly sets `force_tier: 3` in config or says \"use tier 3\"\n- Otherwise: NEVER routes to Tier 3\n\nModel: anthropic/claude-opus-4 (when enabled)\n\n### Rule D → USER OVERRIDE\nIf `force_tier` is set in config (1, 2, or 3), honor it unconditionally for the session.\nWhen force_tier is null (default), normal Rules A/B apply.\n\n### Rule E → CACHE HIT\nIf the same prompt hash was seen in the last 60 minutes:\n- Reuse prior output\n- Skip all tool calls\n\n### Rule F → ESCALATION (Limited)\nIf Tier 1 produces an unsatisfactory result:\n- Escalate to Tier 2 (one attempt only)\n- Never escalate to Tier 3 unless force_tier: 3 is set\n\n## Tool Call Policy (Strict Minimization)\n\n### Before making ANY tool call, check:\n1. Can this be answered from current context/memory? → Skip tool call.\n2. Can this be answered from cached results? → Skip tool call.\n3. Is the tool call essential to answer the prompt? → Proceed.\n\n### Tool call rules:\n- **File reads:** Only read files explicitly referenced or clearly needed. Never pre-load docs, old memory, or knowledge base speculatively.\n- **File writes:** Only when the user requests a create/edit action.\n- **Exec/shell:** Only when the user requests a command or the task requires system interaction.\n- **Web fetch/search:** Only when the user explicitly asks for external data. Never speculative.\n- **Memory search:** Only when the user references prior work, decisions, or history.\n- **Browser:** Only when explicitly requested.\n- **Email/message:** Only for scheduled sends (daily digest) or explicit user requests.\n\n### Per-session tool call budget:\n- Target: ≤3 tool calls for simple prompts (Tier 1)\n- Target: ≤6 tool calls for moderate prompts (Tier 2)\n- If approaching budget, prefer answering from context over making additional calls.\n\n## Context Loading Policy\n\n| Tier | Always Load | Conditionally Load | Never Load |\n|------|------------|-------------------|------------|\n| 1    | SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md | — | Everything else |\n| 2    | SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md | memory/TODAY.md (if relevant), TOOLS.md (if tools mentioned) | Old memory, docs, knowledge |\n| 3    | N/A (disabled) | N/A | N/A |\n\n## Budget Guardrails\n\n- If daily spend exceeds 80% of daily allocation → force all remaining calls to Tier 1\n- If daily spend exceeds 95% → emergency mode: Tier 1 only, no tool calls unless user-initiated\n- Monthly budget: $20.00 (configurable)\n\n## Logging (Lean)\n\nEach call logs:\n- timestamp\n- chosen_tier (1 or 2)\n- model_used\n- tokens_in / tokens_out\n- tool_calls_count\n- cached (true/false)\n- fallback_used (true/false)\n- fallback_provider (name)\n\nExcluded from logs:\n- Raw prompts (hashed only)\n- Force-tier status (not surfaced in digest)\n\n## Privacy\n\n- No raw prompts stored\n- Logs auto-purge after 30 days\n- No data leaves local environment except scheduled email digest\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":363,"output":1229,"cacheRead":40832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42424,"cost":{"input":-363,"output":-1229,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1592}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772328647262}}
