{"type":"message","id":"a2bbf3f8","parentId":"5882b57c","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:31:08.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Summarizing updates**\n\nI want to summarize the changes we've made and confirm that a test wasn't requested. I should mention the fallback configuration has been updated and that we’re leaning on policy. It’s important to ask if there are any further tweaks needed and provide clear next steps. Also, I’ll include a caution about handling sensitive information. Overall, it’s about making sure everything is clear and properly communicated. Let's get to it!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Noted. Here’s what I’ve done and what to expect:\n\nWhat I updated just now\n- Routing policy\n  - ROUTING_POLICY.md updated to Lean v2 with Free-First fallbacks\n  - Tier 1 defaults to the cheapest; Tier 2 is keyword-triggered; Tier 3 remains off unless explicitly enabled\n  - Free-first path will try google-gemini-pro-3.1-preview and gpt-5.3-codex before OpenRouter, with spillover only when needed\n  - Tool calls minimized by policy (only when necessary)\n  - Force tier override remains available per session (not surfaced in the digest)\n  - Added fallback logging fields (fallback_used, fallback_provider)\n- Configuration\n  - Copilot config updated at: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/config/copilot-pro.json\n  - Includes: email, 08:30 digest time, budget, default_tier, routing_rules, digest_depth, attachment, drilldown\n  - New fields: fallback_provider (free-first), fallback_settings (provider order), force_tier (default null)\n- Daily digest scaffolding\n  - Daily digest script wired to produce high-level digest with a drill-down Markdown attachment\n  - Output reports located at: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/reports/\n- New lean daily report script\n  - /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n  - Generates a high-level digest and a detailed MD attachment for drill-down\n\nWhat this means for you\n- You’ll still get the daily digest at 08:30 (local) with high-level content and a Markdown drill-down attachment.\n- The routing logic will prioritize free providers first for Tier 1/2, spilling over to paid OpenRouter only if needed (e.g., rate-limited or failure of free providers).\n- Tier 3 remains off by default; you can enable it via force_tier if you decide to test it later.\n- A non-OpenRouter fallback path is in place, with explicit provider order and logging to indicate when a fallback was used.\n\nOptional test preview\n- You asked not to run a test. I won’t trigger a test email, but I can generate a local test digest file if you want to review formatting before the live schedule hits.\n\nWhat I need from you (quick recap)\n- Nothing else for now unless you want to tweak:\n  - The free providers order (you gave Google Gemini Pro 3.1 Preview first, then GPT-5.3 Codex)\n  - Whether to show fallback usage in the daily digest (currently set to log but not surface in the digest)\n  - If you want Tier 2 to be triggerable by a specific keyword list (we can adjust the ROUTING_POLICY accordingly)\n\nNext steps (optional)\n- I can run a dry-run digest locally and place the high-level digest in reports for your review (without emailing it).\n- If you’d like, I can also add a one-line note in the daily digest whenever a fallback was used and which provider took the load.\n\nWould you like me to prepare a dry-run digest file now for your review, or wait for the 08:30 live digest tomorrow?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":41413,"output":854,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43547,"cost":{"input":-41413,"output":-854,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-42267}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772328663813}}
