{"type":"message","id":"4c8ca9af","parentId":"7b6b336c","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:40:42.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Proposing email solutions**\n\nI think we should respond with empathy and suggest some workarounds for the user. One option is to modify the subject and body to avoid using the bot's name, or allowing for an approval workflow. I can also offer to adjust the email-sending configuration to sanitize the content. I’ll provide steps to change the skill to use a placeholder or remove the \"OpenCopilot Pro\" name. Keeping it concise is essential, and no tool calls are needed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Thanks for the heads up. If the bot name is triggering a rejection, I can adjust the test email to remove or mask branding and use a neutral sender/subject.\n\nOptions:\n- A) Rename the test email and body to be branding-free (e.g., subject: Daily Digest Preview, body: brief summary).\n- B) Add an approval gate: the test email is held for your manual approval before sending.\n- C) Use a neutral sender (no bot name) and a generic subject, but keep the same content.\n\nWhat would you prefer?\n- I can re-send a branding-free preview right away, or\n- Enable a simple “approve-before-send” toggle in config and hold the test until you OK it.\n\nIf you’d like, I’ll implement option A now (neutral subject/body) and re-send the preview."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":29106,"output":331,"cacheRead":15232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44669,"cost":{"input":-29106,"output":-331,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-29437}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772329237911}}
