{"type":"message","id":"ddffdb00","parentId":"7d35a4de","timestamp":"2026-03-01T01:42:05.090Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Proposing Email Changes**\n\nThe user mentioned that the bot’s name in the email address is causing rejections. So, I’m considering suggesting a change to a more neutral \"From\" display name and email. I can't change the real email, but I could propose using something like \"OpenCopilot Preview\" as the sender name while keeping the email unchanged. We could also set up a masking option, like using an alias. I’ll provide a plan and ask for confirmation to proceed!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. The issue is the sender/display name including the bot branding. I can fix it by sending the test from a neutral sender and/or masking the bot name.\n\nOptions (choose one or mix):\n- A) Neutral sender/name for test: use a neutral From name (e.g., OpenCopilot Preview) and a neutral subject/body. Then re-send the branding-free preview.\n- B) Approval gate: hold the test mail until you approve the sender/name first.\n- C) Use a dedicated alias: send from a non-bot address (if you have an alias you can authorize).\n\nI can implement A now (neutral subject/body + neutral sender) and re-send the preview. Confirm and I’ll proceed."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":29073,"output":463,"cacheRead":15616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45152,"cost":{"input":-29073,"output":-463,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-29536}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772329318653}}
