{"type":"message","id":"9bc37987","parentId":"a4611e32","timestamp":"2026-03-01T02:11:27.147Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning troubleshooting steps**\n\nI want to respond with a clear plan to troubleshoot the issue and suggest alternatives. There’s no need for tool use here. First, I should acknowledge the blocking problem and propose steps like checking email deliverability, confirming a neutral sender, and reviewing SPF/DKIM settings. It might also help to suggest a fallback method, like manually pasting or saving to a local file to email later. I'll ask for any error details to provide a quick checklist. Let's move forward!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"That sounds like a deliverability block. Here’s a quick plan to get unblocked or work around it:\n\n- Check bounce/error reason: Look for any bounce codes or messages from the mail gateway (spam rejection, SPF/DKIM fail, domain blocked, recipient-domain rules). If you can share the bounce text, I can diagnose faster.\n- Neutral sender verification: If the neutral sender (OpenCopilot Preview) is still being blocked, try a different neutral alias or a plain-from address that’s already approved in your org.\n- Privacy/branding issue: If branding is triggering filtering, we can further mask content and sender details, and keep the subject/body ultra-plain.\n- Alternate delivery path:\n  - Local preview: Save the digest as a Markdown file in a known path (no email) and I’ll paste the body here for you to review.\n  - Manual email op: I can craft the exact MIME/SMTP snippet you can run from a trusted network to trigger delivery via your usual workflow.\n- Debug steps I can run (with your OK):\n  - Attempt a second test with a different neutral sender (e.g., “OpenCopilot Preview 2”) and a plain subject.\n  - Try via a different channel (e.g., a secure internal chat message or a test webhook) if email remains blocked.\n  - Temporarily disable attachments and send a plain-text digest to rule out attachment-related blocks.\n\nTell me which route you want:\n- A) Re-run a second neutral sender test with a different alias\n- B) Deliver as a local file for you to open\n- C) Use an alternate delivery channel (if available)\n- D) Skip until the email route is fixed and proceed with in-app previewes\n\nIf you can share the bounce message, I’ll tailor the fix immediately."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":44550,"output":535,"cacheRead":1536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46621,"cost":{"input":-44550,"output":-535,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-45085}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772331082418}}
