{"type":"message","id":"57248d3f","parentId":"5e955032","timestamp":"2026-03-01T03:34:59.117Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Providing email validation steps**\n\nI think we should respond with reassurance and gather specific details from the user. My plan is to validate deliverability by setting up checks and potentially implementing a test digest to their personal email. I’ll suggest verifying MX, SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, as well as handling bounces. It’s a good idea to create a test email, track it, and maybe use an email testing tool while keeping logs. I’ll mention that we won't send anything until confirmed and ask for permission to run a dry-run. Let's keep it concise!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Thanks for the heads up. Since you haven’t sent anything yet, we can sanity-check deliverability before sending any real digests.\n\nWhat I propose\n- Validate the email path: confirm MX records, SPF, DKIM, and DMARC for luv2worship@gmail.com (or your domain if you’re routing through G Suite).\n- Do a dry-run to that address: send a branding-free test digest (no attachments or with a sanitized attachment) just to verify inbox routing, not content.\n- Monitor bounce behavior: if you see any undeliverables, capture the bounce reason and adjust (e.g., SPF alignment, mailbox full, temporary block).\n- Use a safe test channel first: if you’re worried about deliverability, we can forward the test to a secondary address you trust or save as a local preview first.\n\nQuestions\n- Do you want me to run a dry-run test to luv2worship@gmail.com now?\n- Should I also add a simple bounce-detection step and a retry policy (e.g., 2 retries with a backoff)?\n- Is there a preferred branding/subject for test emails to differentiate from the real daily digest?\n\nIf you approve, I’ll trigger a branding-free test to luv2worship@gmail.com and report back with results (delivered, bounced with reason, or queued)."}],"api"