kills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py >> /home/ec2-user/logs/daily_digest.log 2>&1\n  - If you want the daily digest to continue at 08:30, keep that separate; the 4-hour cadence can run a secondary preview check or a test window.\n- If you prefer systemd timers (more robust on some servers):\n  - Create two timers and two service units that run the same Python scripts on a 4-hour interval.\n\nWhat to put in the wrapper scripts\n- Wrapper 1: dry_run_digest.py\n  - Steps:\n    - Run the branding-free test (the same test we sent recently)\n    - Capture output (success/failure, any bounce notes)\n    - Email or save a local report as a plain Markdown/HTML digest to review\n- Wrapper 2: daily_digest.py (or reuse generate_daily_report.py with a date window)\n  - Steps:\n    - Generate the digest for the current window\n    - Email the preview to luv2worship@gmail.com\n    - Do not override the live 08:30 digest (optional: you can gate this with a flag)\n\nWhat I need from you to finalize\n- Do you want these to run under your user crontab (crontab -e) or via systemd timers?\n- Confirm file paths for the two wrappers:\n  - dry_run_digest.py path\n  - generate_daily_report.py path (already exists)\n- Do you want both tasks to log their results to a central log file or email you a short status per run?\n\nIf you’d like, I can draft the two wrapper scripts for you and provide exact crontab/systemd unit samples you can paste in."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":47775,"output":1014,"cacheRead":2944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51733,"cost":{"input":-47775,"output":-1014,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-48789}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772339061448}}
