{"type":"message","id":"98fc5263","parentId":"aa006fa0","timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:32:54.613Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Examining the Discrepancy**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in dissecting this email delivery puzzle. It appears that bounce messages are originating from `austin.king@parallon.com`, a discrepancy the user has highlighted. My configuration should be using a separate Gmail address. I need to pinpoint the source of these misdirected notifications; potential cron job configuration errors or other background process settings are now primary concerns.\n\n\n**Debugging the Source**\n\nI've homed in on the core issue: the script is likely using `smtplib`, bypassing the intended Gmail skill. This explains the `austin.king@parallon.com` bounces, sent directly from the local machine. My investigation has now shifted toward confirming the script's email configuration and rectifying the `gmail` skill integration to resolve this delivery failure.\n\n\n**Verifying the Script's Method**\n\nI've examined the `generate_daily_report.py` script and the suspicions seem confirmed. It appears the email functionality is using `smtplib` and attempting to send mail directly, which would explain the `austin.king@parallon.com` bounces. It is highly probable that the `gmail` skill is not being correctly implemented. My next action is to integrate the `gmail` skill's API into the script, to ensure the mail is delivered through the proper channels.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_read_3fiGrCx8dTTKUTGvNI2K","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py"},"thoughtSignature":"{\"index\":0,\"id\":\"tool_read_3fiGrCx8dTTKUTGvNI2K\",\"type\":\"reasoning.encrypted\",\"data\":\"\",\"format\":\"google-gemini-v1\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":2273,"output":893,"cacheRead":52773,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55939,"cost":{"input":-2273,"output":-893,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-3166}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772375563405}}
{"type":"message","id":"48f59f0e","parentId":"98fc5263","timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:32:54.636Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_read_3fiGrCx8dTTKUTGvNI2K","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nOpenCopilot Pro — Daily Token Usage Report Generator\n\nReads OpenClaw session logs, computes token usage/cost by model tier,\nand produces a Markdown digest (high-level + drilldown attachment).\n\nOutput: writes report to ../reports/YYYY-MM-DD.md\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport glob\nimport hashlib\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# ── Paths ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nSKILL_DIR   = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent\nCONFIG_PATH = Path(os.environ.get(\n    \"COPILOT_CONFIG\",\n    os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/workspace/config/copilot-pro.json\")\n))\nLOG_DIR     = Path(os.environ.get(\n    \"OPENCLAW_LOG_DIR\",\n    os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/logs\")\n))\nREPORT_DIR  = SKILL_DIR / \"reports\"\nREPORT_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n# ── Tier classification (mirrors ROUTING_POLICY.md) ───────────────────\nTIER_MAP = {\n    # Tier 1 — cheap\n    \"claude-haiku\":       1, \"claude-3-haiku\":    1, \"claude-haiku-4\": 1,\n    \"gemini-flash\":       1, \"gemini-2.0-flash\":  1,\n    # Tier 2 — mid\n    \"claude-sonnet\":      2, \"claude-sonnet-4\":   2, \"claude-3.5-sonnet\": 2,\n    \"gpt-4o\":             2, \"gpt-4o-mini\":       1,\n    # Tier 3 — expensive\n    \"claude-opus\":        3, \"claude-opus-4\":     3,\n    \"o1\":                 3, \"o1-preview\":        3, \"gpt-5.3-codex\": 3,\n}\n\n# Cost per 1K tokens (input/output) — rough estimates, USD\nCOST_PER_1K = {\n    1: {\"input\": 0.00025, \"output\": 0.00125},\n    2: {\"input\": 0.003,   \"output\": 0.015},\n    3: {\"input\": 0.015,   \"output\": 0.075},\n}\n\n\ndef load_config():\n    if CONFIG_PATH.exists():\n        with open(CONFIG_PATH) as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    return {\n        \"email\": \"austin.king@parallon.com\",\n        \"report_time\": \"08:30\",\n        \"budget_monthly_usd\": 20.00,\n        \"default_tier\": \"tier-1\",\n        \"digest_depth\": \"high-level\",\n        \"attachment_format\": \"markdown\",\n        \"drilldown\": True,\n    }\n\n\ndef classify_model(model_name: str) -> int:\n    \"\"\"Return tier (1/2/3) for a model string.\"\"\"\n    lower = model_name.lower()\n    for key, tier in TIER_MAP.items():\n        if key in lower:\n            return tier\n    # Unknown model → assume Tier 2\n    return 2\n\n\ndef scan_logs(target_date: datetime.date) -> list:\n    \"\"\"\n    Scan OpenClaw log files for entries matching target_date.\n    Returns list of dicts with keys: model, tokens_in, tokens_out, timestamp, prompt_hash.\n    \"\"\"\n    entries = []\n    date_str = target_date.isoformat()\n\n    # Try JSON-lines logs\n    for pattern in [str(LOG_DIR / \"*.jsonl\"), str(LOG_DIR / \"*.log\"), str(LOG_DIR / \"**/*.jsonl\")]:\n        for fpath in glob.glob(pattern, recursive=True):\n            try:\n                with open(fpath) as f:\n                    for line in f:\n                        line = line.strip()\n                        if not line or not line.startswith(\"{\"):\n                            continue\n                        try:\n                            rec = json.loads(line)\n                        except json.JSONDecodeError:\n                            continue\n                        ts = rec.get(\"timestamp\", rec.get(\"ts\", rec.get(\"time\", \"\")))\n                        if date_str not in str(ts):\n                            continue\n                        model = rec.get(\"model\", rec.get(\"model_id\", \"unknown\"))\n                        tok_in = int(rec.get(\"tokens_input\", rec.get(\"prompt_tokens\", rec.get(\"input_tokens\", 0))))\n                        tok_out = int(rec.get(\"tokens_output\", rec.get(\"completion_tokens\", rec.get(\"output_tokens\", 0))))\n                        prompt = rec.get(\"prompt\", rec.get(\"messages\", \"\"))\n                        p_hash = hashlib.sha256(str(prompt).encode()).hexdigest()[:12]\n                        entries.append({\n                            \"model\": model,\n                            \"tier\": classify_model(model),\n                            \"tokens_in\": tok_in,\n                            \"tokens_out\": tok_out,\n                            \"timestamp\": ts,\n                            \"prompt_hash\": p_hash,\n                        })\n            except Exception:\n                continue\n    return entries\n\n\ndef compute_stats(entries: list, config: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Aggregate entries into stats dict.\"\"\"\n    total_in = sum(e[\"tokens_in\"] for e in entries)\n    total_out = sum(e[\"tokens_out\"] for e in entries)\n    total_tokens = total_in + total_out\n\n    tier_counts = {1: 0, 2: 0, 3: 0}\n    tier_tokens = {1: 0, 2: 0, 3: 0}\n    tier_cost = {1: 0.0, 2: 0.0, 3: 0.0}\n    model_usage = {}\n\n    for e in entries:\n        t = e[\"tier\"]\n        tier_counts[t] += 1\n        tier_tokens[t] += e[\"tokens_in\"] + e[\"tokens_out\"]\n        cost = (e[\"tokens_in\"] / 1000) * COST_PER_1K[t][\"input\"] + \\\n               (e[\"tokens_out\"] / 1000) * COST_PER_1K[t][\"output\"]\n        tier_cost[t] += cost\n\n        m = e[\"model\"]\n        if m not in model_usage:\n            model_usage[m] = {\"calls\": 0, \"tokens\": 0, \"cost\": 0.0}\n        model_usage[m][\"calls\"] += 1\n        model_usage[m][\"tokens\"] += e[\"tokens_in\"] + e[\"tokens_out\"]\n        model_usage[m][\"cost\"] += cost\n\n    total_cost = sum(tier_cost.values())\n    total_calls = sum(tier_counts.values())\n    budget = config.get(\"budget_monthly_usd\", 20.0)\n    daily_budget = budget / 30\n    budget_pct = (total_cost / daily_budget * 100) if daily_budget > 0 else 0\n\n    # Efficiency: % of calls handled by Tier 1\n    efficiency = (tier_counts[1] / total_calls * 100) if total_calls > 0 else 0\n\n    return {\n        \"total_tokens\": total_tokens,\n        \"total_in\": total_in,\n        \"total_out\": total_out,\n        \"total_cost\": total_cost,\n        \"total_calls\": total_calls,\n        \"tier_counts\": tier_counts,\n        \"tier_tokens\": tier_tokens,\n        \"tier_cost\": tier_cost,\n        \"model_usage\": model_usage,\n        \"efficiency_pct\": efficiency,\n        \"budget_monthly\": budget,\n        \"budget_daily\": daily_budget,\n        \"budget_used_pct\": budget_pct,\n        \"entries\": entries,\n    }\n\n\ndef build_highlevel(stats: dict, date: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Build the high-level email body.\"\"\"\n    tc = stats[\"tier_counts\"]\n    total = stats[\"total_calls\"] or 1\n    lines = [\n        f\"# 🤖 OpenCopilot Daily Digest — {date}\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Summary\",\n        f\"- **Total calls:** {stats['total_calls']}\",\n        f\"- **Total tokens:** {stats['total_tokens']:,} ({stats['total_in']:,} in / {stats['total_out']:,} out)\",\n        f\"- **Estimated cost:** ${stats['total_cost']:.4f}\",\n        f\"- **Daily budget used:** {stats['budget_used_pct']:.1f}% of ${stats['budget_daily']:.2f}/day (${stats['budget_monthly']:.2f}/mo)\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Efficiency\",\n        f\"- **Tier 1 (cheap):** {tc[1]} calls ({tc[1]/total*100:.0f}%)\",\n        f\"- **Tier 2 (mid):** {tc[2]} calls ({tc[2]/total*100:.0f}%)\",\n        f\"- **Tier 3 (expensive):** {tc[3]} calls ({tc[3]/total*100:.0f}%)\",\n        f\"- **Efficiency grade:** {stats['efficiency_pct']:.0f}% of calls on cheapest tier\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Cost by Tier\",\n        f\"- Tier 1: ${stats['tier_cost'][1]:.4f} ({stats['tier_tokens'][1]:,} tokens)\",\n        f\"- Tier 2: ${stats['tier_cost'][2]:.4f} ({stats['tier_tokens'][2]:,} tokens)\",\n        f\"- Tier 3: ${stats['tier_cost'][3]:.4f} ({stats['tier_tokens'][3]:,} tokens)\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Save Tips\",\n    ]\n\n    # Dynamic tips\n    if tc[3] > 0:\n        lines.append(f\"- ⚠️ {tc[3]} Tier 3 calls detected. Review if any could be downgraded to Tier 2.\")\n    if stats[\"efficiency_pct\"] < 50:\n        lines.append(\"- 💡 Less than half your calls used the cheapest tier. Try shorter prompts for simple tasks.\")\n    if stats[\"budget_used_pct\"] > 80:\n        lines.append(\"- 🔴 Budget alert: you've used >80% of today's allocation.\")\n    if stats[\"efficiency_pct\"] >= 70:\n        lines.append(\"- ✅ Great efficiency! Most calls are on the cheapest tier.\")\n    lines.append(\"- 💾 Keep context minimal — only load files when needed.\")\n    lines.append(\"- 🔄 Use cache for repeated prompts within 60 minutes.\")\n    lines.append(\"\")\n    lines.append(\"---\")\n    lines.append(\"*Detailed breakdown attached as Markdown. Open in Obsidian or any MD viewer to drill down.*\")\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n\ndef build_drilldown(stats: dict, date: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Build the detailed Markdown attachment.\"\"\"\n    lines = [\n        f\"# OpenCopilot Detailed Report — {date}\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Model-by-Model Breakdown\",\n        \"\",\n        \"| Model | Tier | Calls | Tokens | Est. Cost |\",\n        \"|-------|------|-------|--------|-----------|\",\n    ]\n    for model, info in sorted(stats[\"model_usage\"].items(), key=lambda x: -x[1][\"cost\"]):\n        tier = classify_model(model)\n        lines.append(f\"| {model} | {tier} | {info['calls']} | {info['tokens']:,} | ${info['cost']:.4f} |\")\n\n    lines.extend([\"\", \"## Call Log (hashed prompts)\", \"\"])\n    lines.append(\"| Time | Model | Tier | Tokens In | Tokens Out | Prompt Hash |\")\n    lines.append(\"|------|-------|------|-----------|------------|-------------|\")\n    for e in stats[\"entries\"]:\n        lines.append(f\"| {e['timestamp']} | {e['model']} | {e['tier']} | {e['tokens_in']:,} | {e['tokens_out']:,} | {e['prompt_hash']} |\")\n\n    lines.extend([\n        \"\",\n        \"## Routing Policy Compliance\",\n        \"\",\n        f\"- Total calls: {stats['total_calls']}\",\n        f\"- Tier 1 target: >60% | Actual: {stats['tier_counts'][1]}/{stats['total_calls']} ({stats['efficiency_pct']:.0f}%)\",\n        f\"- Escalations: check logs for rationale_tag 'escalation-from-tier-X'\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Budget Status\",\n        \"\",\n        f\"- Monthly budget: ${stats['budget_monthly']:.2f}\",\n        f\"- Daily allocation: ${stats['budget_daily']:.2f}\",\n        f\"- Today's spend: ${stats['total_cost']:.4f} ({stats['budget_used_pct']:.1f}%)\",\n        \"\",\n        \"---\",\n        \"*Generated by OpenCopilot Pro — Deterministic Routing Policy v1*\",\n    ])\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n\ndef generate(target_date=None):\n    \"\"\"Main entry point. Returns (highlevel_md, drilldown_md, report_path).\"\"\"\n    config = load_config()\n    if target_date is None:\n        target_date = (datetime.utcnow() - timedelta(days=1)).date()\n\n    entries = scan_logs(target_date)\n    stats = compute_stats(entries, config)\n\n    date_str = target_date.isoformat()\n    highlevel = build_highlevel(stats, date_str)\n    drilldown = build_drilldown(stats, date_str)\n\n    # Save reports\n    hl_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{date_str}-digest.md\"\n    dd_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{date_str}-detailed.md\"\n    hl_path.write_text(highlevel)\n    dd_path.write_text(drilldown)\n\n    print(f\"Reports saved:\\n  {hl_path}\\n  {dd_path}\")\n    return highlevel, drilldown, str(dd_path)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    generate()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772375574628}}
{"type":"message","id":"87e221ca","parentId":"48f59f0e","timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:33:03.943Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right — the bounce is hitting `127.0.0.1` which means something on this box is trying to send email directly through a local MTA (like sendmail/postfix) instead of routing through your Gmail/Maton API. That's not how we should be sending.\n\nThe digest script I built only generates local Markdown files — it doesn't send email on its own. But something else on the system might be trying to forward to austin.king@parallon.com via the local mail daemon.\n\nLet me check what's configured:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_01QfjrvmDJYmAbzATB3pXysR","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"bash -lc 'crontab -l 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; cat /etc/aliases 2>/dev/null | tail -5; echo \"---\"; systemctl is-active postfix 2>/dev/null || echo \"postfix not active\"; systemctl is-active sendmail 2>/dev/null || echo \"sendmail not active\"; echo \"---\"; cat /etc/postfix/main.cf 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"relayhost\\|mydestination\\|inet_interfaces\" | head -10; echo \"---\"; mail -V 2>/dev/null || echo \"no mail cmd\"'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":69822,"output":319,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70141,"cost":{"input":-69822,"output":-319,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-70141}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772375574637}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ba2624e","parentId":"87e221ca","timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:33:04.464Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01QfjrvmDJYmAbzATB3pXysR","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"15 21 * * * /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/export_gmail_daily.sh\n30 21 * * 0 python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/update_personal_snapshot.py >> /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge/email-vault/99_Admin/snapshot-refresh.log 2>&1\nCRON_TZ=America/Chicago\n10 6 * * * /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/send_important_email_digest.sh\n5 6 * * * /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/fetch_and_send_calendar_brief.sh\n20 6 * * 1 python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_weekly_digest.py >> /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge/email-vault/99_Admin/icloud-weekly-digest.log 2>&1\n0 18 * * 1-5 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/send_maintenance_reminder_to_work.sh weekday-evening >> /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge/email-vault/99_Admin/work-mail.log 2>&1\n0 6 * * 6,0 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/send_maintenance_reminder_to_work.sh weekend-morning >> /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge/email-vault/99_Admin/work-mail.log 2>&1\n---\n# trap decode to catch security attacks\ndecode:\t\troot\n\n# Person who should get root's mail\n#root:\t\tmarc\n---\ninactive\npostfix not active\ninactive\nsendmail not active\n---\n---\nno mail cmd"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":512,"aggregated":"15 21 * * * /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/export_gmail_daily.sh\n30 21 * * 0 python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/update_personal_snapshot.py >> /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge/email-vault/99_Admin/snapshot-refresh.log 2>&1\nCRON_TZ=America/Chicago\n10 6 * * * /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/send_important_email_digest.sh\n5 6 * * * /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/fetch_and_send_calendar_brief.sh\n20 6 * * 1 python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_weekly_digest.py >> /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge/email-vault/99_Admin/icloud-weekly-digest.log 2>&1\n0 18 * * 1-5 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/send_maintenance_reminder_to_work.sh weekday-evening >> /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge/email-vault/99_Admin/work-mail.log 2>&1\n0 6 * * 6,0 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/send_maintenance_reminder_to_work.sh weekend-morning >> /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/knowledge/email-vault/99_Admin/work-mail.log 2>&1\n---\n# trap decode to catch security attacks\ndecode:\t\troot\n\n# Person who should get root's mail\n#root:\t\tmarc\n---\ninactive\npostfix not active\ninactive\nsendmail not active\n---\n---\nno mail cmd","cwd":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772375584459}}
{"type":"message","id":"ffd9d295","parentId":"2ba2624e","timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:33:09.257Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found it. You have two cron jobs sending to your work email:\n\n- `send_maintenance_reminder_to_work.sh` — runs weekday evenings (6 PM) and weekend mornings (6 AM)\n\nLet me check what that script does:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_0147rk6vNx5Cqe74Mhnm1vUC","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"bash -lc 'cat /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/send_maintenance_reminder_to_work.sh 2>/dev/null'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":70602,"output":150,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70752,"cost":{"input":-70602,"output":-150,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-70752}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772375584465}}
{"type":"message","id":"3da20f51","parentId":"ffd9d295","timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:33:09.605Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_0147rk6vNx5Cqe74Mhnm1vUC","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\nENV_FILE=\"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_mail.env\"\nif [[ -f \"$ENV_FILE\" ]]; then\n  # shellcheck disable=SC1090\n  source \"$ENV_FILE\"\nfi\n\n: \"${ICLOUD_EMAIL:?ICLOUD_EMAIL missing}\"\n: \"${ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD:?ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD missing}\"\nWORK_EMAIL=\"${WORK_EMAIL:-austin.king@parallon.com}\"\n\nMODE=\"${1:-weekday-evening}\"\nif [[ \"$MODE\" == \"weekend-morning\" ]]; then\n  SUBJECT=\"Weekend Morning Maintenance Reminder\"\n  BODY=\"Good morning Austin — quick maintenance board check: pick one must-do before noon and set one carry-forward for tomorrow.\"\nelse\n  SUBJECT=\"Weekday Evening Maintenance Reminder\"\n  BODY=\"Evening check-in Austin — review your maintenance board, close one small task tonight, and set one carry-forward for tomorrow.\"\nfi\n\nexport ICLOUD_EMAIL ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD WORK_EMAIL SUBJECT BODY\npython3 - <<'PY'\nimport os, smtplib\nfrom email.message import EmailMessage\nmsg = EmailMessage()\nmsg['Subject'] = os.environ['SUBJECT']\nmsg['From'] = os.environ['ICLOUD_EMAIL']\nmsg['To'] = os.environ.get('WORK_EMAIL', 'austin.king@parallon.com')\nmsg.set_content(os.environ['BODY'])\ns = smtplib.SMTP('smtp.mail.me.com', 587)\ns.starttls()\ns.login(os.environ['ICLOUD_EMAIL'], os.environ['ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD'])\ns.send_message(msg)\ns.quit()\nprint('sent')\nPY"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":336,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\nENV_FILE=\"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_mail.env\"\nif [[ -f \"$ENV_FILE\" ]]; then\n  # shellcheck disable=SC1090\n  source \"$ENV_FILE\"\nfi\n\n: \"${ICLOUD_EMAIL:?ICLOUD_EMAIL missing}\"\n: \"${ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD:?ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD missing}\"\nWORK_EMAIL=\"${WORK_EMAIL:-austin.king@parallon.com}\"\n\nMODE=\"${1:-weekday-evening}\"\nif [[ \"$MODE\" == \"weekend-morning\" ]]; then\n  SUBJECT=\"Weekend Morning Maintenance Reminder\"\n  BODY=\"Good morning Austin — quick maintenance board check: pick one must-do before noon and set one carry-forward for tomorrow.\"\nelse\n  SUBJECT=\"Weekday Evening Maintenance Reminder\"\n  BODY=\"Evening check-in Austin — review your maintenance board, close one small task tonight, and set one carry-forward for tomorrow.\"\nfi\n\nexport ICLOUD_EMAIL ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD WORK_EMAIL SUBJECT BODY\npython3 - <<'PY'\nimport os, smtplib\nfrom email.message import EmailMessage\nmsg = EmailMessage()\nmsg['Subject'] = os.environ['SUBJECT']\nmsg['From'] = os.environ['ICLOUD_EMAIL']\nmsg['To'] = os.environ.get('WORK_EMAIL', 'austin.king@parallon.com')\nmsg.set_content(os.environ['BODY'])\ns = smtplib.SMTP('smtp.mail.me.com', 587)\ns.starttls()\ns.login(os.environ['ICLOUD_EMAIL'], os.environ['ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD'])\ns.send_message(msg)\ns.quit()\nprint('sent')\nPY","cwd":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772375589600}}
