{"type":"message","id":"8d6204d2","parentId":"a7e1e7ed","timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:53:12.770Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Guiding environment setup**\n\nI tried to export in the shell, but the new subshell loses the environment variables. To make this work, we really need to set them up in the session. Since the tool executes separate processes, they can't persist. I should instruct the user to run the export in their shell. I’ll also offer to attempt a dry-run here and provide concise updates, including the commands to source the environment file path and next steps.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I can’t persist environment variables across tool sessions, so I can’t reliably export them from here for you. You’ll need to run the export in your current shell where the OpenClaw session is running.\n\nWhat you can run in your shell (one-time in this session)\n- Load from the file you have:\n  - source /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_mail.env\n  - or export individually:\n    - export ICLOUD_EMAIL=\"dougyfresh_bot@icloud.com\"\n    - export ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD=\"hwid-bzvx-jhnv-sojn\"\n- Verify the variables are set:\n  - echo $ICLOUD_EMAIL\n  - echo $ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD (will print asterisks if masked in your shell)\n\nThen retry the branding-free Tier-2 test to luv2worship@gmail.com (or your work address) using the Dougyfresh_bot@icloud.com sender.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also:\n- Generate a fresh branding-free Markdown preview now (no SMTP) so you can review content while you set the credentials.\n- Provide a small, ready-to-run shell snippet you can paste into your session to load the env and retry the send from within your OpenClaw workspace.\n\nWhat would you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":208,"output":425,"cacheRead":65536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66169,"cost":{"input":-208,"output":-425,"cacheRead"