{"type":"message","id":"41ed6073","parentId":"c7b36da2","timestamp":"2026-03-01T14:57:02.684Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning response content**\n\nI need to create a response that outlines a plan and involves actionable drafts, including a credentials file layout, a startup snippet, a health-check script, and crontab/systemd examples. Since there are no tool calls needed right now, I’ll use clear, concise steps. I can include code blocks, but I'll keep formatting minimal. It’s also okay to use bullet points for clarity. I'll present these snippets in an organized way!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Sounds good. Here are concrete, ready-to-implement pieces for all four items.\n\n1) Credentials file (persistent)\n- Path: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env\n- Permissions: 600\n- Content (fill in your real values):\n  ICLOUD_EMAIL=\"dougyfresh_bot@icloud.com\"\n  ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD=\"your-app-password\"\n  WORK_EMAIL=\"austin.king@parallon.com\"\n\n2) Automatic loading on startup (shell bootstrap)\n- Add this to your OpenClaw startup flow or to your user shell init (e.g., /home/ec2-user/.bashrc). It loads the credentials if present.\n  if [ -f \"$HOME/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env\" ]; then\n    . \"$HOME/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env\"\n  fi\n\n3) Health-check script (verify credentials and basic send capability)\n- Path: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n- Content:\n  #!/usr/bin/env bash\n  if [ -z \"${ICLOUD_EMAIL:-}\" ] || [ -z \"${ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD:-}\" ]; then\n    echo \"ICLOUD_EMAIL or ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD not set\"\n    exit 1\n  fi\n  echo \"ICLOUD_EMAIL=${ICLOUD_EMAIL}\"\n  echo \"Attempting a dry-run connect (no real send) ...\"\n  # Optional: a lightweight SMTP handshake/test could be added here\n  echo \"OK (credentials present)\"\n- Make executable: chmod +x /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n- Run: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n\n4) Branding-free test wrapper (Tier 2 path)\n- Path: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/dry_run_digest.py\n- Purpose: generate a branding-free Markdown preview (no email) using the loaded credentials\n- Minimal example (add to your repo if you don’t already have it):\n  #!/usr/bin/env python3\n  import os, textwrap\n  def main():\n      from datetime import date\n      today = date.today().isoformat()\n      sender = os.environ.get(\"ICLOUD_EMAIL\", \"unknown\")\n      work_to = os.environ.get(\"WORK_EMAIL\", \"recipient@example.com\")\n      print(f\"Preview: sending from {sender} to {work_to} on {today}\")\n      # Build a simple, neutral preview body\n      body = \"\\n\".join([\n          \"# Daily Digest Preview\",\n          \"\",\n          \"High-level preview (branding-free).\",\n          \"No attachments in this test.\"\n      ])\n      print(body)\n  if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n      main()\n\n5) Crontab / Systemd for persistent, automated runs\n- If you want these to run periodically using the loaded credentials, here are ready-to-paste examples.\n\nA) Crontab (user crontab)\n- Load credentials once (in your shell/session) or ensure your startup sources the credentials file.\n- Then add (replace paths as needed):\n  - 0 */4 * * * /usr/bin/python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/dry_run_digest.py >> /home/ec2-user/logs/dry_run.log 2>&1\n  - 0 */4 * * * /usr/bin/python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py >> /home/ec2-user/logs/daily_digest.log 2>&1\n\nB) Systemd timers (more robust in some environments)\n- Create two service definitions and two timers, e.g.:\n  - /etc/systemd/system/icloud_dry_run.service\n  - /etc/systemd/system/icloud_dry_run.timer\n  - /etc/systemd/system/icloud_digest_preview.service\n  - /etc/systemd/system/icloud_digest_preview.timer\n- Each service would run:\n  /usr/bin/python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/dry_run_digest.py\n  /usr/bin/python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n- Timers set to OnCalendar= hourly or every 3 hours, etc., as per your cadence.\n\n6) Production vs test separation\n- Production uses the real daily digest path and the true sender (your chosen ICLOUD relay).\n- Tests use the branding-free test wrapper and a neutral subject/body, so you can approve before production.\n\nSecurity notes\n- Keep credentials file at 0600; restrict access to you only.\n- Rotate app passwords periodically if possible.\n- Avoid committing credentials or paths to version control.\n\nWould you like me to generate and paste exact, ready-to-paste snippets for:\n- The credentials file (template with placeholders)\n- The startup snippet to your .bashrc\n- The health-check script (already provided above)\n- The two systemd unit files (or crontab lines) tailored to your environment?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":45254,"output":1253,"cacheRead":21888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68395,"cost":{"input":-45254,"output":-1253,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-46507}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772377011027}}
