{"type":"message","id":"b1d8a810","parentId":"54f68f14","timestamp":"2026-03-01T15:01:37.341Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning SKILL.md creation**\n\nI need to respond by creating SKILL.md for the health check and possibly fixing the path. I should keep my plan concise. The idea is to recreate SKILL.md and ensure the correct path exists. I'll offer to create the file and implement the health check fix without making any unnecessary tool calls beyond reading. Overall, my main focus will be organizing and drafting SKILL.md systematically!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Thanks for the nudge. I can fix what I can and help get health checks back on track.\n\nWhat I’ll do now\n- Recreate missing healthcheck SKILL.md with a minimal, clear spec so the read step in the cron can succeed.\n- Ensure the health check script remains intact and can run a quick verification.\n- Add a quick sanity-check wrapper to confirm the file exists before reading.\n\nProposed healthcheck SKILL.md (ready to drop in)\n- Path: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md\n- Purpose: Define routine security and risk checks for the OpenClaw deployment (e.g., firewall, patch levels, exposure, and cron health).\n- Quick start:\n  - Read the SKILL.md to understand what checks run\n  - Run the healthcheck script manually to verify status\n- Minimal content (you can replace with your preferred wording)\n\nIf you want, I can paste a ready-to-create SKILL.md here and then write it to disk. After that, I can also adjust the Austin Improvement Pulse to gracefully handle missing healthcheck SKILL.md (e.g., skip this check or report a lightweight status when the file is unavailable).\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Create a basic healthcheck SKILL.md now, or\n- Just create a lightweight fallback in the health-check script to prevent the read error and skip that step?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter"