{"type":"message","id":"da87dc1b","parentId":"57b80f97","timestamp":"2026-03-01T15:02:56.071Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Creating SKILL.md content**\n\nI need to create a minimal SKILL.md file, keeping it simple with just the basic sections. I should also modify the read guard in the script and adjust the healthcheck script to ensure it doesn’t fail if SKILL.md is missing. The user wants to proceed with creating SKILL.md now, so I'll focus on writing that simple Markdown. Afterward, I will respond to the user with confirmation and outline the next steps.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_yHEINARPDQGCbBMfKiSZE7rP","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md","content":"# Health Check Skill - Minimal\n\nPurpose: Define a lightweight health check suite for the OpenClaw deployment (security posture, patch level visibility, exposure checks, cron health).\n\n## Quick Start\n- Read this file to understand what checks run.\n- Run the health check script to verify status: \n  - Path: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n  - Command: bash /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n\n## Checks (minimal)\n- Verify environment: required env vars (ICLOUD_EMAIL, ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD)\n- Verify access to mail relay (icloud path) when configured\n- Basic connectivity check to ensure the cron task can run in the future\n\n## Maintenance\n- Update this SKILL.md when checks change\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":49237,"output":365,"cacheRead":22144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71746,"cost":{"input":-49237,"output":-365,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-49602}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772377370941}}
