{"type":"message","id":"1f62467f","parentId":"3dac52c4","timestamp":"2026-03-01T15:03:05.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning health check response**\n\nI need to summarize the situation regarding the health_check script. Earlier, it was located at /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh, but now it’s missing. I can suggest creating a minimal health check script and confirming the update in SKILL.md. I’ll include steps to recreate the script and ensure cron uses it. I also need to mention that the test run indicates a missing file. I'll provide a plan and ask if further actions are confirmed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Thanks. I created a minimal Health Check SKILL.md, but the actual icloud_health_check.sh script is missing in your filesystem right now. I’ll fix that and put a safe, lightweight health check in place.\n\nWhat I’ve done just now\n- Added /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md (minimal health-check spec).\n- Attempted to run the health check script, but the file /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh is not present.\n\nWhat I’ll do next (quick, safe steps)\n1) Recreate a minimal icloud_health_check.sh\n   - Purpose: verify credentials (ICLOUD_EMAIL/ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD) exist and the icloud relay path is loadable.\n   - Basic checks: print loaded env values (mask password), confirm ability to read the env file if used, and return a success or a clear error.\n\n2) Wire a safe read-guard for Austin Improvement Pulse\n   - If healthcheck SKILL.md exists, the cron should read it; if not, skip with a lightweight status instead of failing.\n\n3) Re-run a dry health check\n   - After the script exists, run bash /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh manually to verify it reports OK or the exact issue.\n\nProposed minimal health check script (to drop in)\n- Path: /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n- Content (safe, minimal):\n\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\nENV_FILE=\"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env\"\nif [[ -f \"$ENV_FILE\" ]]; then\n  source \"$ENV_FILE\"\nfi\n\nif [[ -z \"${ICLOUD_EMAIL:-}\" || -z \"${ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD:-}\" ]]; then\n  echo \"ICLOUD_EMAIL or ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD not set\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"ICLOUD_EMAIL=${ICLOUD_EMAIL}\"\necho \"Credentials loaded: OK\"\nexit 0\n\nWould you like me to drop that script in and then attempt to run it? If you approve, I’ll place the script, make it executable, and run it to confirm a healthy setup."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":70170,"output":647,"cacheRead":1536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72353,"cost":{"input":-70170,"output":-647,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-70817}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772377378490}}
