{"type":"message","id":"05d10d7e","parentId":"eb5b83d1","timestamp":"2026-03-01T15:03:44.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Addressing tool formatting issues**\n\nI'm encountering some trouble with tool formatting. Instead of trying to execute a tool, I think it's better to provide a clear explanation and offer a snippet that the user can run themselves. I'll share the exact content of the script along with concise steps to execute it. I should acknowledge that the tool attempt failed, so I’ll give a simple script block that the user can paste in directly. Heavy formatting should be avoided, but a bullet list is fine for clarity.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I can’t reliably run the script creation tool here due to a quoting issue, but here is the exact script content you can paste into a file yourself. This will create the health check, load credentials from a persistent file, and be safe to run.\n\nWhat to do:\n- Create the script file with this content\n- Make it executable\n- Ensure the credentials file at /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env exists and is correct\n- Run the script to verify\n\nScript content to paste into /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh:\n\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\nENV_FILE=\"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env\"\nif [[ -f \"$ENV_FILE\" ]]; then\n  . \"$ENV_FILE\"\nfi\n\nif [[ -z \"${ICLOUD_EMAIL:-}\" || -z \"${ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD:-}\" ]]; then\n  echo \"ICLOUD_EMAIL or ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD not set\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"ICLOUD_EMAIL=${ICLOUD_EMAIL}\"\necho \"Credentials loaded: OK\"\n\nMake it executable:\nchmod +x /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n\nWhat this gives you:\n- A lightweight, persistent health check that verifies credentials exist\n- A safe read path for the cron step that previously failed due to missing SKILL.md\n- A quick way to confirm the iCloud relay path could be used for later sends\n\nIf you want, I can also provide a minimal health-check wrapper that prints a friendly status to the console and returns 0 on success, or expand the health check to attempt a very lightweight, non-destructive SMTP handshake when credentials exist."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":702,"output":526,"cacheRead":72320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73548,"cost":{"input":-702,"output":-526,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1228}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772377418969}}
