{"type":"message","id":"49d8d2d1","parentId":"0e021597","timestamp":"2026-03-01T15:08:09.822Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Updating script for dry-run**\n\nI think we should implement a dry-run function by default. The script will be updated to have TEST_SEND set to 1, but we won’t actually send anything because of credentials issues. I’ll modify the script to set TEST_SEND=1 and ensure it uses WORK_EMAIL from the environment. I’ll also remind to load the credentials. After that, I can ask if they want me to run it or just prepare the script content. Let’s get that ready!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Understood. Here’s a ready-to-paste, dry-run-enabled version of the health check. It will perform the SMTP handshake and, on success, also attempt a harmless dry-run email to WORK_EMAIL.\n\nPaste this to /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh (overwrite the old file), then make executable and run.\n\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nENV_FILE=\"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env\"\nif [[ -f \"$ENV_FILE\" ]]; then\n  . \"$ENV_FILE\"\nfi\n\nif [[ -z \"${ICLOUD_EMAIL:-}\" || -z \"${ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD:-}\" ]]; then\n  echo \"ERROR: ICLOUD_EMAIL or ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD not set\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"ICLOUD_EMAIL=${ICLOUD_EMAIL}\"\necho \"Starting SMTP handshake (iCloud relay)...\"\n\npython3 - <<'PY'\nimport smtplib, ssl, os\nuser = os.environ.get(\"ICLOUD_EMAIL\")\npw = os.environ.get(\"ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD\")\nrecipient = os.environ.get(\"WORK_EMAIL\", \"\")\nhost = \"smtp.mail.me.com\"\nport = 587\ntry:\n    with smtplib.SMTP(host, port, timeout=20) as s:\n        s.ehlo()\n        s.starttls(context=ssl.create_default_context())\n        s.ehlo()\n        s.login(user, pw)\n        code, msg = s.noop()\n        print(\"SMTP NOOP response:\", code, msg.decode() if isinstance(msg, (bytes, bytearray)) else msg)\n        # Dry-run send (enabled by default)\n        if recipient:\n            msg_text = f\"\"\"From: {user}\nTo: {recipient}\nSubject: Health Check: ICLOUD relay OK (dry-run)\n\nThis is a lightweight health-check test message.\n\"\"\"\n            s.sendmail(user, [recipient], msg_text)\n            print(\"Dry-run test email sent to\", recipient)\n        print(\"OK: SMTP handshake and login succeeded\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(\"ERROR: SMTP health check failed:\", str(e))\n    raise\nPY\n\nchmod +x /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n\nNotes\n- Load credentials in your session first:\n  - source /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env\n- Ensure WORK_EMAIL is set to your work address (austin.king@parallon.com for example) if you want the dry-run to go there.\n- Run the check:\n  - /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/icloud_health_check.sh\n\nWould you like me to also display a quick summary of the test results here after you run it, or should I keep delivering just the pass/fail signals?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":51820,"output":749,"cacheRead":22784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75353,"cost":{"input":-51820,"output":-749,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-52569}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772377679036}}
