{"type":"message","id":"b28d103d","parentId":"fd08e498","timestamp":"2026-03-01T15:10:18.105Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Addressing authentication issues**\n\nI need to respond about the authentication issue we encountered. It seems the health check failed because the mailbox doesn't exist. My next steps will involve verifying that the WORK_EMAIL is correct, ensuring the iCloud email is allowed, and checking that the recipient is accurate. I'll also confirm that the app password is valid and suggest trying a different recipient. Lastly, I'm thinking about updating the environment and rerunning. I'll summarize these results for the user clearly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Thanks for the update. The dry-run SMTP handshake attempted to authenticate, but it failed: 550 5.1.1 Mailbox does not exist. That usually means the recipient address in the dry-run path is invalid or the sender account isn’t allowed to access that mailbox.\n\nWhat I recommend next (quick options)\n- Double-check recipient: Make sure WORK_EMAIL is set to a valid inbox you own (e.g., a real work address like austin.king@parallon.com) and that this mailbox exists.\n- Confirm sender privileges: The Dougyfresh_bot@icloud.com account must be allowed to send to that recipient via the iCloud relay (some setups require whitelisting).\n- Validate credentials: Ensure ICLOUD_EMAIL and ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD are correct for the iCloud relay, and that the app password is still active.\n- Test with a known-good recipient: Try sending the dry-run to a mailbox you know exists (e.g., your own personal account) to isolate whether the issue is the recipient or the sender path.\n- If needed, disable the dry-run mail attempt (don’t send a real test yet) and keep the handshake-only result for now.\n\nWhat I can do next\n- Update the health check to only attempt the dry-run when WORK_EMAIL is a valid, known-good address.\n- Add a quick-preview step that prints the intended recipient and subject without actually sending, so you can confirm before a real send.\n- If you provide a working recipient, I can rerun the test immediately and report the exact status (delivered vs bounced with reason).\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Change the health check to use a confirmed recipient (or skip the dry-run unless you approve a real address), or\n- Try with a different recipient that you know is valid?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":1026,"output":503,"cacheRead":76032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77561,"cost":{"input":-1026,"output":-503,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1529}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772377812867}}
