{"type":"message","id":"53b6f77b","parentId":"378f1154","timestamp":"2026-03-01T15:52:12.733Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning email response steps**\n\nThe user needs a summary of the next steps after running a health check, which showed a 550 error indicating the mailbox doesn't exist. I should suggest verifying that the recipient exists and ensuring correct SMTP relay usage. It might help to adjust settings, such as using only handshake or disabling dry-run. Also, I'll mention the need to set TEST_SEND and correct WORK_EMAIL credentials. It’s crucial I present these options concisely and not run any more tools unless specifically asked.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Here’s where we stand after the latest run:\n\n- Credentials loaded: ICLOUD_EMAIL set to dougyfresh_bot@icloud.com; WORK_EMAIL set to austin.king@parallon.com; APP_PASSWORD placeholder in place (your real password is needed for the SMTP login).\n- SMTP handshake attempt against the iCloud relay failed with 550 Mailbox does not exist when trying the dry-run recipient.\n\nWhat this means\n- The mailbox in the dry-run path (the recipient being used during the test) is not valid for that sender, so the test can’t complete as-is.\n- The handshake itself may still be okay, but we can’t confirm deliverability until we fix the recipient path or avoid sending to that recipient.\n\nWhat I can do next (your call)\nOption A: Use a known-good recipient for the dry-run\n- Set WORK_EMAIL to an address that you know exists and can receive mail (e.g., a personal Gmail or a work alias that you’ve verified).\n- Then re-run the health check with TEST_SEND enabled to verify a real delivery path.\n\nOption B: Keep dry-run disabled for now (only handshake)\n- Run the health check again with dry-run disabled (no TEST_SEND) to confirm the SMTP login/NOOP works without attempting a send.\n- I’ll report the handshake result, not an email.\n\nOption C: