{"type":"message","id":"4147a7f4","parentId":"34a59ae6","timestamp":"2026-03-01T16:08:14.954Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning for password update**\n\nI need to update the iCloud Mail environment after a password reset, but I don't have the new password yet. I could try a handshake with a placeholder, though. Running a health check again using handshake only won't work since the credentials are invalid. I think prompting the user for the new password is a good idea. I'll lay out a plan to retry once the password is provided and confirm that the recipient is austin.king@parallon.com.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Understood. I’ll proceed with the plan and pause on the actual dry-run until you provide the new app password.\n\nWhat I’m doing now\n- Waiting for the new iCloud app password to finish the reset flow.\n- Once you supply it, I’ll:\n  - Update /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/credentials/icloud_mail.env with the new password\n  - Reload credentials in this session\n  - Run the health check in handshake-only mode first\n  - If the handshake succeeds, enable the dry-run test to austin.king@parallon.com\n  - Report the outcome and any retry steps\n\nWhat I need from you\n- The new iCloud app password (or confirmation I should fetch it from a vault).\n- Confirm the dry-run recipient remains austin.king@parallon.com.\n\nOptional: I can also run a handshake-only health check immediately with the current credentials (likely to fail until the new password is set) and report the exact error to help troubleshoot. Do you want me to run that now as a diagnostic pass?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":81273,"output":539,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83092,"cost":{"input":-81273,"output":-539,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-81812}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772381286329}}
