{"type":"message","id":"776819b4","parentId":"9c01a231","timestamp":"2026-03-01T17:24:57.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Generating Apple iCloud App Password**\n\nI need to outline the steps for generating an Apple iCloud app password. First, go to Apple ID, then Security, and select App-Specific Passwords. After that, generate a password and name it something like \"Dougyfresh bot email.\" It's also important to mention the need for two-factor authentication and that this feature should be used on a compatible device. Additionally, I could suggest using a Google app password. Lastly, remember to store the password securely in an environment file!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Here’s how to generate a new iCloud App-Specific Password:\n\n- Sign in to your Apple ID account (appleid.apple.com) or on your iPhone/iPad using the same Apple ID you use for iCloud.\n- Go to Security.\n- Under App-Specific Passwords, choose Generate Password.\n- Enter a label (e.g., \"OpenClaw Dougyfresh\") and Generate.\n- Copy the 16-character password that appears (you won’t see it again).\n- Update your icloud_mail.env with ICLOUD_APP_PASSWORD=<the new password>.\n- Save and reload in your session (source the env file or re-run your health check).\n\nNotes:\n- You may need two-factor authentication enabled to access App-Specific Passwords.\n- If you don’t see App-Specific Passwords, ensure your Apple ID has 2FA turned on and you’re using the correct account.\n- Store the new password securely and don’t share it in plain text.\n\nWould you like me to provide a small one-liner to update the env file once you paste the new password?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":81159,"output":402,"cacheRead":1792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83353,"cost":{"input":-81159,"output":-402,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-81561}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":177238