{"type":"message","id":"450b23f5","parentId":"070ec6c7","timestamp":"2026-03-01T17:54:32.375Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Implementing code updates**\n\nI need to implement updates for the code by providing a snippet for `generate_daily_report.py` that works with the Gmail/MATON flow. I should also explain how to test it and what results to expect without running external APIs. I can create a paste-ready script with a placeholder path for Gmail and simulate the functionality of sending an email via a hypothetical library. It's essential to create a wrapper function, `send_email_via_maton`, to safely call the Gmail skill. I'll include clear TODO placeholders too!**Preparing script content**\n\nI’m ready to create a script that’s easy to paste. It will include a function to build a digest and create temporary files. Then, I’ll call `maton_send_email` using the API key stored in the environment variable `MATON_API_KEY`. I also need to update the skill or configuration to enable the recipient and ensure the sender's display name is neutral, showing as \"OpenCopilot Digest.\" I'll present the code snippet and outline the steps for testing it. Let’s move forward!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Implementing Gmail/MATON flow in generate_daily_report.py (paste-ready)\n\nWhat this does\n- Builds the digest content (high-level body + detailed Markdown attachment) as before.\n- Uses a Gmail/MATON API path to send the email:\n  - Authenticates with MATON API key from environment.\n  - Sends from the actual account behind the scenes (austin.king@parallon.com).\n  - Displays the sender as a neutral name (OpenCopilot Digest) in the UI.\n  - Keeps corporate recipient (austin.king@parallon.com) as the test recipient for now.\n- Keeps the code separate from the previous SMTP path (no iCloud SMTP usage here).\n\nWhat to paste into /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nOpenCopilot Pro — Daily Token Usage Report Generator (Gmail/MATON API path)\n\nGenerates a high-level digest and a Markdown-detailed attachment.\nSends via Gmail/MATON API path (authenticated behind the scenes).\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nimport hashlib\nfrom datetime import datetime, date\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Paths and config\nSKILL_DIR = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent\nCONFIG_PATH = Path(os.environ.get(\n    \"COPILOT_CONFIG\",\n    os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/workspace/config/copilot-pro.json\")\n))\nREPORT_DIR = SKILL_DIR / \"reports\"\nREPORT_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\ndef load_config():\n    if CONFIG_PATH.exists():\n        with open(CONFIG_PATH) as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    return {\n        \"email\": \"austin.king@parallon.com\",  # primary test recipient\n        \"report_time\": \"08:30\",\n        \"budget_monthly_usd\": 20.0,\n        \"digest_depth\": \"high-level\",\n        \"attachment_format\": \"markdown\",\n        \"drilldown\": True,\n        \"display_sender\": \"OpenCopilot Digest\",\n        \"recipient_list\": [\"austin.king@parallon.com\"]\n    }\n\ndef build_digest_content(date_str, depth=\"high-level\"):\n    lines = []\n    lines.append(f\"# OpenCopilot Daily Digest — {date_str}\")\n    lines.append(\"\")\n    lines.append(\"## Summary\")\n    lines.append(\"- Placeholder summary (replace with actual data in real run).\")\n    lines.append(\"- Total calls: 0\")\n    lines.append(\"- Total tokens: 0 in / 0 out\")\n    lines.append(\"- Estimated cost: $0.0000\")\n    lines.append(\"\")\n    if depth == \"high-level\":\n        lines.append(\"## High-level Notes\")\n        lines.append(\"- This is a test of the Gmail/MATON path.\")\n        lines.append(\"- Attachments will render in supporting mail clients.\")\n    else:\n        lines.append(\"## Details (drill-down)\")\n        lines.append(\"Detailed breakdown would go here.\")\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\ndef write_attachment(content_text, date_str):\n    # Write the detailed Markdown attachment\n    detail_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{date_str}-detailed.md\"\n    detail_path.write_text(content_text)\n    return detail_path\n\ndef send_via_maton(to_list, subject, body_text, attachment_path, display_sender=\"OpenCopilot Digest\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Placeholder for Gmail/MATON API send.\n    In a real environment, this would call the MATON Gmail path, e.g. via a Python client\n    that wraps the Gmail API, using MATON_API_KEY from env.\n    Expected behavior:\n      - Use MATON API key from env\n      - Send from the internal account (behind the scenes)\n      - Set From display to `display_sender`\n      - Attach the file at attachment_path if provided\n      - Return a dict with status, message, and maybe an API ID\n    \"\"\"\n    maton_key = os.environ.get(\"MATON_API_KEY\")\n    if not maton_key:\n        return {\"status\": \"error\", \"message\": \"MATON_API_KEY not configured\"}\n    # This is a placeholder; replace with actual API call in your environment.\n    return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"message\": f\"Mock send to {to_list} via Gmail/MATON with display '{display_sender}'\"}\n\ndef main():\n    cfg = load_config()\n    today = date.today().isoformat()\n    # Build high-level digest and attachment\n    digest_text = build_digest_content(today, depth=cfg.get(\"digest_depth\",\"high-level\"))\n    attachment_md = write_attachment(digest_text, today)\n\n    # Email details\n    to_list = cfg.get(\"recipient_list\", [\"austin.king@parallon.com\"])\n    subject = f\"OpenCopilot Digest — {today}\"\n    body_text = digest_text  # for mail body; could be a shorter summary if desired\n\n    # Send via MATON Gmail path\n    result = send_via_maton(\n        to_list=to_list,\n        subject=subject,\n        body_text=body_text,\n        attachment_path=str(attachment_md),\n        display_sender=cfg.get(\"display_sender\",\"OpenCopilot Digest\")\n    )\n\n    # Simple log/output\n    if result.get(\"status\") == \"ok\":\n        print(\"SEND_OK:\", result.get(\"message\", \"sent\"))\n        print(f\"Digest delivered to: {', '.join(to_list)}\")\n    else:\n        print(\"SEND_FAIL:\", result.get(\"message\", \"unknown error\"))\n        raise SystemExit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n\nNotes\n- This is a scaffold. In your environment you’ll need a real Gmail/MATON API client invocation inside send_via_maton, replacing the placeholder.\n- Ensure MATON_API_KEY exposure is safe in your runtime (it is read from the environment; you can passport it through a secure vault if needed).\n- If you want multi-recipient delivery or different display logic, adjust the cfg[\"recipient_list\"] and cfg[\"display_sender\"] accordingly.\n\nWhat to test after you paste this\n- Set MATON_API_KEY in the environment (or load via your usual method).\n- Ensure austin.king@parallon.com is in cfg[\"recipient_list\"].\n- Run the script:\n  - python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n- Expectation: The script should attempt to send via Gmail/MATON (the placeholder will need the real API call). In your environment, you should see a success message or a helpful API error message.\n\nWould you like me to add a real MATON Gmail call skeleton (with an explicit API call block) in the same function, or keep it as a clean integration point for your team to plug in the actual library you use?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":68875,"output":1958,"cacheRead":27264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98097,"cost":{"input":-68875,"output":-1958,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-70833}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772387660940}}
