{"type":"message","id":"3b1a8a49","parentId":"4b1b0461","timestamp":"2026-03-01T17:56:00.633Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Below is the full script for `generate_daily_report.py` that now includes a concrete skeleton for sending via the Gmail/MATON API using the `requests` library. This code will work once you replace the placeholder URL and payload details with the exact endpoint and field names required by the MATON Gmail API.\n\n**Paste this into** `/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py`\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nOpenCopilot Pro — Daily Token Usage Report Generator (Gmail/MATON API)\n\nCreates a high‑level digest and a detailed Markdown attachment,\nthen sends the email via the MATON Gmail API.\n\nPrerequisites\n--------------\n* MATON_API_KEY must be set in the environment.\n* The MATON Gmail API endpoint and request format must be known.\n  Replace `MATON_GMAIL_ENDPOINT` and the payload structure below\n  with the actual values from the MATON documentation.\n\nThe script keeps a neutral display sender (\"OpenCopilot Digest\")\nwhile authenticating as the real corporate account\n(austin.king@parallon.com).\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nimport hashlib\nimport base64\nimport requests\nfrom datetime import datetime, date\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# ── Configuration paths ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nSKILL_DIR   = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent\nCONFIG_PATH = Path(os.environ.get(\n    \"COPILOT_CONFIG\",\n    os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/workspace/config/copilot-pro.json\")\n))\nREPORT_DIR  = SKILL_DIR / \"reports\"\nREPORT_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n# ── Load configuration (fallback defaults) ─────────────────────────────────\ndef load_config():\n    if CONFIG_PATH.exists():\n        with open(CONFIG_PATH) as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    # Default configuration if the file is missing\n    return {\n        \"email\": \"austin.king@parallon.com\",      # primary test recipient\n        \"report_time\": \"08:30\",\n        \"budget_monthly_usd\": 20.0,\n        \"digest_depth\": \"high-level\",\n        \"attachment_format\": \"markdown\",\n        \"drilldown\": True,\n        \"display_sender\": \"OpenCopilot Digest\",\n        \"recipient_list\": [\"austin.king@parallon.com\"]\n    }\n\n# ── Build the high‑level digest (placeholder data) ────────────────────────\ndef build_digest_content(date_str, depth=\"high-level\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    In a real deployment you would pull token usage stats and\n    construct the summary. Here we use placeholder data.\n    \"\"\"\n    lines = [\n        f\"# OpenCopilot Daily Digest — {date_str}\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Summary\",\n        \"- Placeholder summary (replace with real stats).\",\n        \"- Total calls: 0\",\n        \"- Total tokens: 0 in / 0 out\",\n        \"- Estimated cost: $0.0000\",\n        \"\"\n    ]\n    if depth == \"high-level\":\n        lines.extend([\n            \"## High‑level Notes\",\n            \"- This is a test of the Gmail/MATON send path.\",\n            \"- Attachments will render in supporting mail clients.\"\n        ])\n    else:\n        lines.extend([\n            \"## Detailed (drill‑down)\",\n            \"- Detailed breakdown would be placed here.\"\n        ])\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n# ── Write detailed Markdown attachment file ───────────────────────────────\ndef write_attachment(content_text, date_str):\n    \"\"\"Write detailed Markdown file and return its path.\"\"\"\n    detail_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{date_str}-detailed.md\"\n    detail_path.write_text(content_text)\n    return detail_path\n\n# ── Send email via MATON Gmail API ────────────────────────────────────────\ndef send_via_maton(to_list, subject, body_text, attachment_path,\n                   display_sender=\"OpenCopilot Digest\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Sends an email via the MATON Gmail API.\n    Parameters:\n        to_list          – list of recipient email strings\n        subject          – email subject line\n        body_text        – plain‑text body of the email\n        attachment_path  – path to the Markdown file to attach\n        display_sender   – the friendly name shown in the From header\n\n    Returns a dict with keys:\n        status  – \"ok\" or \"error\"\n        message – human‑readable description\n    \"\"\"\n\n    # --------------------------------------------------------------\n    # 1️⃣  Gather required auth and endpoint information\n    # --------------------------------------------------------------\n    maton_key = os.getenv(\"MATON_API_KEY\")\n    if not maton_key:\n        return {\"status\": \"error\", \"message\": \"MATON_API_KEY not set in environment\"}\n\n    # Replace the URL below with the actual MATON Gmail endpoint.\n    # For illustration we use a placeholder.\n    MATON_GMAIL_ENDPOINT = \"https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send\"\n\n    # --------------------------------------------------------------\n    # 2️⃣  Prepare the multipart/form‑data payload\n    # --------------------------------------------------------------\n    # We follow the pattern used by other MATON‑based tools:\n    #   - `Authorization: Bearer <MATON_API_KEY>`\n    #   - Form fields: `from`, `to`, `subject`, `text`, `file` (optional)\n    # The `from` field can contain a display name that the API will\n    # format as:  \"OpenCopilot Digest <austin.king@parallon.com>\"\n    # (the exact syntax depends on the MATON spec; adjust if needed).\n\n    from_header = f\"{display_sender} <{os.getenv('ICLOUD_EMAIL', 'austin.king@parallon.com')}>\"\n\n    files = {\n        \"file\": (os.path.basename(attachment_path), open(attachment_path, \"rb\"), \"text/markdown\")\n    }\n\n    data = {\n        \"from\": from_header,\n        \"to\": \", \".join(to_list),\n        \"subject\": subject,\n        \"text\": body_text,\n        # Additional optional fields (e.g., `html`) can be added here.\n    }\n\n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {maton_key}\"\n    }\n\n    # --------------------------------------------------------------\n    # 3️⃣  Perform the HTTP POST request\n    # --------------------------------------------------------------\n    try:\n        response = requests.post(\n            MATON_GMAIL_ENDPOINT,\n            headers=headers,\n            data=data,\n            files=files,\n            timeout=30   # seconds\n        )\n        # Clean up the opened file handle\n        files[\"file\"][1].close()\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return {\"status\": \"error\", \"message\": f\"Network/Request error: {exc}\"}\n\n    # --------------------------------------------------------------\n    # 4️⃣  Interpret the API response\n    # --------------------------------------------------------------\n    # The MATON API typically returns JSON with a `status` field.\n    # Adjust the parsing below based on the actual response format.\n    try:\n        resp_json = response.json()\n    except Exception:\n        # Non‑JSON response (e.g., plain text error)\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"error\",\n            \"message\": f\"Unexpected response (code {response.status_code}): {response.text[:200]}\"\n        }\n\n    # Example expected structure:\n    #   { \"status\": \"ok\", \"message\": \"Sent\", \"id\": \"<msg-id>\" }\n    if resp_json.get(\"status\") == \"ok\":\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"message\": resp_json.get(\"message\", \"Sent via MATON Gmail\")}\n    else:\n        # Capture any error description the API provides\n        err_msg = resp_json.get(\"error\", resp_json.get(\"message\", \"Unknown error\"))\n        return {\"status\": \"error\", \"message\": f\"MATON API error: {err_msg}\"}\n\n# ── Main execution flow ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndef main():\n    cfg = load_config()\n    today_str = date.today().isoformat()\n\n    # Build digest text and write the detailed attachment\n    digest_body = build_digest_content(today_str, depth=cfg.get(\"digest_depth\", \"high-level\"))\n    attachment_file = write_attachment(digest_body, today_str)\n\n    # Email parameters\n    recipients = cfg.get(\"recipient_list\", [\"austin.king@parallon.com\"])\n    subject = f\"OpenCopilot Digest — {today_str}\"\n    body_text = digest_body   # For now we put the same content into the body\n\n    # Send through MATON Gmail API\n    result = send_via_maton(\n        to_list=recipients,\n        subject=subject,\n        body_text=body_text,\n        attachment_path=str(attachment_file),\n        display_sender=cfg.get(\"display_sender\", \"OpenCopilot Digest\")\n    )\n\n    # Report outcome (stdout is captured by your cron or whatever driver you use)\n    if result[\"status\"] == \"ok\":\n        print(\"SEND_OK:\", result[\"message\"])\n        print(\"Delivered to:\", \", \".join(recipients))\n    else:\n        print(\"SEND_FAIL:\", result[\"message\"])\n        # Exit with non‑zero code so a cron job can notice the failure\n        raise SystemExit(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n### What you need to adjust for a real send\n\n1. **MATON Gmail endpoint**  \n   Replace `MATON_GMAIL_ENDPOINT` with the exact URL the MATON service exposes for sending Gmail messages (e.g., `https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send` or another version). Check MATON’s API docs for the correct path.\n\n2. **Field names**  \n   Confirm the form‑field names (`from`, `to`, `subject`, `text`, `file`) match the MATON specification. Some APIs expect `html` instead of `text`, or may require a separate `body` field.\n\n3. **Authentication header**  \n   The script uses the typical `Authorization: Bearer <MATON_API_KEY>` format. If MATON uses a different header (e.g., `X‑API‑Key`) replace accordingly.\n\n4. **Response handling**  \n   The parsing assumes the API returns JSON with a top‑level `status` key set to `\"ok\"` on success. Adjust the parsing logic if your API uses a different schema (`success`, `code`, `message`, etc.).\n\n5. **Display sender**  \n   The `from_header` composes a display name plus the real email address (`austin.king@parallon.com`). If the API wants a separate `displayName` field, pull that out and send accordingly.\n\n### How to test\n\n```bash\n# Ensure MATON_API_KEY is exported in your shell\nexport MATON_API_KEY=\"your-maton-api-key\"\n\n# Run the script\npython3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n```\n\n- On success you’ll see:\n  ```\n  SEND_OK: <Message returned by MATON>\n  Delivered to: austin.king@parallon.com\n  ```\n- On failure you’ll see a `SEND_FAIL:` line with the error description, which can include authentication errors, missing fields, or network issues.\n\n### Next steps\n\n- **If the test succeeds**, you can schedule the script via cron (or your existing scheduling mechanism) to run at your desired frequency (e.g., every 3 hours). The script already writes the Markdown files under `reports/` for reference if you need them later.\n- **If you need multiple recipients** (e.g., also send to `luv2worship@gmail.com`), just add that address to `recipient_list` in `copilot-pro.json` or modify the `cfg[\"recipient_list\"]` array in the script.\n\nLet me know once you’ve updated the endpoint/field names and run the script, and we’ll review the result together. If you hit any errors, paste the output here and we’ll refine the call."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":99846,"output":2497,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102343,"cost":{"input":-99846,"output":-2497,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-102343}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772387713352}}
