{"type":"message","id":"71e9294d","parentId":"051d4712","timestamp":"2026-03-01T18:02:17.705Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It looks like the script ran silently. That usually means either:\n\n- The script completed without hitting the `print` statements (e.g., it exited early or an exception was swallowed), or\n- The environment didn’t have the required `MATON_API_KEY` or endpoint, so the function returned early without a visible message.\n\nLet’s troubleshoot step‑by‑step:\n\n### 1. Verify environment variables\nRun these commands in the same shell where you’ll execute the script:\n\n```bash\necho \"MATON_API_KEY: ${MATON_API_KEY:-<missing>}\"\necho \"ICLOUD_EMAIL: ${ICLOUD_EMAIL:-<missing>}\"\n```\n\nYou should see the actual API key printed (or at least “<missing>” if it’s not set). If the key is missing, the script will exit early with no output.\n\n### 2. Add explicit debug prints\nWe can add a few `print` statements at the top of the script to confirm it’s being executed and to show the config values.\n\nAdd the following lines right after the imports (or just run a quick one‑liner before the script runs):\n\n```bash\npython3 - <<'PY'\nimport os, json\nprint(\"=== DEBUG START ===\")\nprint(\"MATON_API_KEY present:\", bool(os.getenv(\"MATON_API_KEY\")))\nprint(\"ICLOUD_EMAIL:\", os.getenv(\"ICLOUD_EMAIL\", \"none\"))\n# Load config to see recipients:\ncfg_path = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.openclaw/workspace/config/copilot-pro.json\")\nif os.path.exists(cfg_path):\n    with open(cfg_path) as f:\n        cfg = json.load(f)\n        print(\"Config recipients:\", cfg.get(\"recipient_list\"))\nelse:\n    print(\"Config file missing\")\nprint(\"=== DEBUG END ===\")\nPY\n```\n\nIf you see the debug output, that confirms the environment is set up.\n\n### 3. Run the script in verbose mode\nTemporarily modify the script to force a print at the very end, even if the send fails:\n\n```python\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    try:\n        main()\n    except SystemExit as e:\n        print(\"Exited with code\", e.code)\n    except Exception as ex:\n        print(\"Unexpected error:\", ex)\n```\n\n### 4. Check the log files\nIf you have a cron or other scheduler, it might be redirecting stdout/stderr to a log file. Look in `/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/logs/` or any file you configured for script output.\n\n### 5. Confirm the endpoint and payload\nIf the `MATON_GMAIL_ENDPOINT` placeholder is still pointing to a non‑existent URL, the `requests.post` call will raise a connection error, which is caught and returned as a `SEND_FAIL` message. Ensure you replace:\n\n```python\nMATON_GMAIL_ENDPOINT = \"https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send\"\n```\n\nwith the exact URL from MATON’s documentation.\n\n### Quick test you can run now\n\n1. **Set the API key** (replace `YOUR_KEY` with your real key):\n   ```bash\n   export MATON_API_KEY=\"YOUR_KEY\"\n   ```\n\n2. **Run a minimal test script** that only attempts the POST (no file attachment):\n   ```bash\n   python3 - <<'PY'\nimport os, requests, json\nkey = os.getenv(\"MATON_API_KEY\")\nif not key:\n    print(\"Missing MATON_API_KEY\")\n    raise SystemExit(1)\n\nendpoint = \"https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send\"  # replace if needed\npayload = {\n    \"from\": \"OpenCopilot Digest <austin.king@parallon.com>\",\n    \"to\": \"austin.king@parallon.com\",\n    \"subject\": \"Test from MATON\",\n    \"text\": \"Hello – this is a test email from OpenCopilot.\"\n}\nheaders = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key}\"}\nresp = requests.post(endpoint, headers=headers, data=payload, timeout=15)\nprint(\"HTTP status:\", resp.status_code)\ntry:\n    print(\"Response JSON:\", resp.json())\nexcept Exception:\n    print(\"Raw response:\", resp.text)\nPY\n   ```\n\n   - If the request succeeds you’ll see a JSON response with a success status.\n   - If it fails (e.g., 401, 403, 404), the printed HTTP status and response body will give a clue.\n\n### What to do next\n\n- **If the debug prints show the API key and config**, and the minimal test above returns a clear success JSON, then the full script will work—just run the full script again.\n- **If the minimal test returns an error**, share the HTTP status and response body here; we can adjust the endpoint or payload accordingly.\n- **If the API key is missing**, supply it (export MATON_API_KEY=…) and retry.\n\nLet me know the results of the debug prints or the minimal test. Once we have a successful API response, the full `generate_daily_report.py` will send the digest as intended.**✅ Quick Summary — What’s happening and next steps**\n\n### What we tried\n- Added a **MATON/Gmail API skeleton** to `generate_daily_report.py`.\n- Set up the script to:\n  1. Build a placeholder digest.\n  2. Write a Markdown attachment.\n  3. **Send** via the MATON Gmail endpoint (`https://gateway.maton.ai/google‑mail/v1/send`), using `MATON_API_KEY` for auth.\n- We **ran the script** but got **no output**—meaning it exited before printing the “SEND_OK”/“SEND_FAIL” messages.\n\n### Why no output?\nThe script only prints messages **after** it attempts the API call. If:\n- **`MATON_API_KEY` is missing**, the function returns early with `{\"status\":\"error\",\"message\":\"MATON_API_KEY not configured\"}` – but we didn’t see that printed because the script aborted before the final `print`.\n- **The endpoint URL is still a placeholder**, or the request fails with a connection error, the function catches it and returns an error dict. If the script raised an exception that wasn’t caught (or we didn’t see the exception), we’d get no output.\n- The script might have **exited silently** (e.g., `SystemExit` with no print statements) if a required variable was missing.\n\n### What we need to confirm\n1. **`MATON_API_KEY` is actually set** in the environment where the script runs.\n2. **The endpoint URL is correct** (the placeholder may need to be replaced with the real MATON Gmail API endpoint you have access to).\n3. **The request payload format** (field names, `from`, `to`, `subject`, `text`, `file`) matches what the MATON API expects.\n\n### Immediate troubleshooting steps (run them in the same shell)\n\n```bash\n# 1️⃣ Verify the API key is present\necho \"MATON_API_KEY → ${MATON_API_KEY:-<MISSING>}\"\n\n# 2️⃣ Verify the sender email (used in the From header)\necho \"ICLOUD_EMAIL → ${ICLOUD_EMAIL:-<MISSING>}\"\n```\n\nIf **both values print** (the key should be a long alphanumeric string; the email should be `austin.king@parallon.com`), we can move on.\n\n---\n\n### Minimal “raw” test – see exactly what the MATON API returns\n\n```bash\npython3 - <<'PY'\nimport os, requests, json\n\nkey = os.getenv(\"MATON_API_KEY\")\nif not key:\n    print(\"❌ MATON_API_KEY missing\")\n    raise SystemExit(1)\n\n# 👉 Replace this URL with the exact MATON Gmail endpoint you have.\nendpoint = \"https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send\"\n\npayload = {\n    \"from\": \"OpenCopilot Digest <austin.king@parallon.com>\",\n    \"to\": \"austin.king@parallon.com\",\n    \"subject\": \"MATON test email\",\n    \"text\": \"Hello – this is a quick test from OpenCopilot.\"\n}\nheaders = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key}\"}\n\nprint(\"🔧 Sending test request …\")\nresp = requests.post(endpoint, headers=headers, data=payload, timeout=15)\n\nprint(\"📊 HTTP status:\", resp.status_code)\ntry:\n    print(\"🗂️ JSON response:\", resp.json())\nexcept Exception:\n    print(\"⚠️ Not JSON – raw reply:\", resp.text[:200])\nPY\n```\n\n**What you’ll see**\n- `HTTP status: 200` → Great! The API accepted the request.\n- Any **error code** (`401`, `403`, `404`, `422`, …) tells us exactly why it’s failing (invalid token, wrong endpoint, missing fields, etc.).\n- The **JSON payload** will contain a `status` field (`\"ok\"` or `\"error\"`) and a helpful message.\n\n---\n\n### If the test **succeeds**\n\n1. **Leave the endpoint URL as‑is** (or update it if you have a more specific one).\n2. **Run the full script again**:\n\n```bash\npython3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n```\n\nYou should now see:\n\n```\nSEND_OK: <message from MATON>\nDelivered to: austin.king@parallon.com\n```\n\nThe email will land in the corporate inbox with the high‑level body and the attached Markdown file.\n\n---\n\n### If the test **fails**\n\n- **401/403** → Invalid or missing `MATON_API_KEY`. Double‑check the key, its scopes, and that it’s not expired.\n- **404** → Wrong endpoint URL. Verify the exact path from MATON’s docs (e.g., maybe it’s `.../gmail/v1/sendMessage`).\n- **422** → Payload mismatch. Check that field names (`from`, `to`, `subject`, `text`) match what the API expects. Some APIs require `html` instead of `text`, or a separate `file` multipart field.\n- **5xx** → Service‑side problem. You may need to retry later or contact MATON support.\n\n---\n\n### Quick “one‑liner” to see why we got **no output** earlier\n\nAdd a tiny debug line at the very top of `generate_daily_report.py` (just after the imports) and re‑run:\n\n```python\nprint(\"🚀 Starting generate_daily_report – MATON_API_KEY set?\", bool(os.getenv(\"MATON_API_KEY\")))\n```\n\nIf that prints, we know the script is actually executing. If you still see nothing, the script may be exiting **before** reaching that line (e.g., because of a `Permission denied` on the file, or because Python couldn’t read the script). Double‑check file permissions:\n\n```bash\nchmod +x /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\nls -l /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n```\n\nMake sure it’s readable/executable by the user running the script.\n\n---\n\n### TL;DR – What to do right now\n\n1. **Run the environment check** (`echo $MATON_API_KEY` and `echo $ICLOUD_EMAIL`). Confirm they’re set.\n2. **Run the minimal test** (the block above) and paste the output here.\n3. **If the test succeeds**, run the full `generate_daily_report.py` again and you should see the `SEND_OK` message and receive the email.\n4. **If it fails**, share the HTTP status and response; we’ll adjust the endpoint/payload accordingly.\n\nOnce we nail down a successful API call, the daily digest will be reliably sent via Gmail/MATON, eliminating the iCloud SMTP roadblocks we hit earlier. Let me know the results of the quick test, and we’ll get the final email in your inbox!"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":102518,"output":2545,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105063,"cost":{"input":-102518,"output":-2545,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-105063}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772388058951}}
