specify a different URL\npayload = {\n  \"from\": \"OpenCopilot Digest <austin.king@parallon.com>\",\n  \"to\": \"austin.king@parallon.com\",\n  \"subject\": \"MATON test email\",\n  \"text\": \"Hello – this is a test from OpenCopilot.\"\n}\nheaders = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key}\"} if key else {}\nprint(\"Key present:\", bool(key))\nresp = requests.post(endpoint, headers=headers, data=payload, timeout=15)\nprint(\"HTTP status:\", resp.status_code)\ntry:\n  print(\"Response JSON:\", resp.json())\nexcept Exception:\n  print(\"Raw response:\", resp.text[:400])\nPY\n- Share the HTTP status and any JSON body you get.\n- If you see 401/403, key/scope issue; 404/5xx, endpoint issue; 200/201 with JSON, you’re good.\n\n3) If raw test passes, run the real script\n- Ensure executable:\n  - chmod +x /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n- Run:\n  - python3 /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/opencopilot-pro/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\n- Share the output. You should see SEND_OK and Delivered to: austin.king@parallon.com.\n\nWhat I’ll do after you give results\n- If raw test fails: I’ll pin down endpoint, payload fields, and authorization header, and provide a precise patch.\n- If raw test succeeds but the daily script still errors: I’ll adjust the script to match your MATON API’s exact payload shape (e.g., field names, multipart handling, or a dedicated sendMessage call).\n- If you want a second recipient tested later, I’ll add that to recipient_list and wire multi-recipient sending.\n\nWant me to proceed with applying a more exact MATON-Gmail call patch now based on typical MATON schemas, or wait for your test results first?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":17797,"output":891,"cacheRead":28416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47104,"cost":{"input":-17797,"output":-891,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-18688}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1